Cut the hide-and-seek.

287
00:19:31,623 --> 00:19:32,581
Tadaka!

288
00:19:36,623 --> 00:19:37,623
She was here a second ago.

289
00:19:38,248 --> 00:19:39,831
[panting]

290
00:19:42,290 --> 00:19:43,540
[Screaming]

291
00:19:43,831 --> 00:19:44,873
Who are you? Stop.

292
00:19:45,081 --> 00:19:45,956
Who are these guys?

293
00:19:46,623 --> 00:19:47,415
Stop.

294
00:19:47,498 --> 00:19:48,290
Statue.

295
00:19:48,373 --> 00:19:49,290
Don't come closer.

296
00:19:49,623 --> 00:19:50,915
I... I will...

297
00:19:51,248 --> 00:19:52,581
- [Screaming]
- [growling]

298
00:19:52,665 --> 00:19:54,498
- [Hissing]
- [growling]

299
00:19:56,248 --> 00:19:57,540
Veeran... let him go.

300
00:19:58,040 --> 00:19:59,665
You brought a human here.

301
00:19:59,998 --> 00:20:01,123
He came here by mistake.

302
00:20:01,206 --> 00:20:03,456
Yakshasan refused to eat the animal.

303
00:20:03,748 --> 00:20:04,790
He's been starving for years.

304
00:20:05,456 --> 00:20:06,748
Let's hand him over to Yakshasan instead.

305
00:20:06,831 --> 00:20:07,665
No.

306
00:20:08,081 --> 00:20:10,998
Handing him over to Yakshasan
isn't your decision to make.

307
00:20:11,081 --> 00:20:13,498
Then you can't decide his fate either.

308
00:20:15,623 --> 00:20:16,915
[loud thud]

309
00:20:17,623 --> 00:20:18,706
[high-pitched tone]

310
00:20:18,790 --> 00:20:19,665
Alok?

311
00:20:21,623 --> 00:20:22,540
Are you alright?

312
00:20:23,373 --> 00:20:26,123
[Breathing Heavily]

313
00:20:35,123 --> 00:20:36,665
He's awake. Let him go.

314
00:20:37,123 --> 00:20:38,581
Tadaka broke a rule.

315
00:20:39,540 --> 00:20:41,206
She brought a human here.

316
00:20:41,540 --> 00:20:43,540
He came here by mistake. Let him go.

317
00:20:43,998 --> 00:20:45,831
He can't leave.

318
00:20:45,915 --> 00:20:47,290
Why? What did he do wrong?

319
00:20:47,665 --> 00:20:48,873
It's forbidden to bring him here.

320
00:20:48,956 --> 00:20:50,831
He doesn't know about us.

321
00:20:51,623 --> 00:20:53,706
He didn't see anything.

322
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:55,706
He knows nothing. Just let him go.

323
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:56,831
How can we just let him go?

324
00:20:56,915 --> 00:20:57,706
[growling]

325
00:21:00,623 --> 00:21:03,206
Hi, I'm Alok Goyal,

326
00:21:03,290 --> 00:21:04,748
reporter, Azad News!

327
00:21:05,623 --> 00:21:06,581
Nice personality.

328
00:21:07,540 --> 00:21:09,956
One of my reels went viral,
you've probably seen it.

329
00:21:10,290 --> 00:21:11,540
It goes like this:

330
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:15,498
A graveyard watchman turns
into a monster, so beware,

331
00:21:15,581 --> 00:21:16,665
[growling]

332
00:21:16,998 --> 00:21:18,081
Alok, Alok...

333
00:21:18,873 --> 00:21:19,706
Quiet.

334
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:20,915
What?

335
00:21:21,123 --> 00:21:21,998
Keep quiet.

336
00:21:22,081 --> 00:21:22,873
Qui--

337
00:21:22,956 --> 00:21:24,248
We should burn him alive.

338
00:21:24,623 --> 00:21:25,373
- No.
- What are you saying?

339
00:21:25,456 --> 00:21:26,581
We should burn him alive.

340
00:21:26,665 --> 00:21:27,581
What is he saying?

341
00:21:27,623 --> 00:21:29,040
He wants to burn you alive.

342
00:21:29,206 --> 00:21:30,415
He wants you to bathe me?

343
00:21:30,915 --> 00:21:32,915
Go ahead, I'm feeling really sticky.

344
00:21:32,998 --> 00:21:33,790
Shush.

345
00:21:34,290 --> 00:21:36,081
[high-pitched tone]

346
00:21:36,956 --> 00:21:37,706
[Gasping]

347
00:21:39,081 --> 00:21:40,081
Uncle, like seriously, what's she saying?

348
00:21:40,915 --> 00:21:41,915
Straight to the gallows?

349
00:21:42,415 --> 00:21:43,790
Who does that?
Let's just talk this through.

350
00:21:44,123 --> 00:21:44,956
I want a lawyer.

351
00:21:45,456 --> 00:21:46,415
He's human.

352
00:21:46,498 --> 00:21:47,540
His blood is poisonous.

353
00:21:47,915 --> 00:21:48,790
We should let him go.

354
00:21:48,873 --> 00:21:49,581
No!

355
00:21:49,873 --> 00:21:50,998
No way, Jose!

356
00:21:51,248 --> 00:21:52,206
Yes! Yes, please!

357
00:21:52,331 --> 00:21:53,248
What are you doing?!

358
00:21:53,498 --> 00:21:55,123
He wants to free you...

359
00:21:55,206 --> 00:21:56,165
WHAT?!

360
00:21:56,581 --> 00:21:58,081
He wants to free you...

361
00:21:58,790 --> 00:21:59,623
He wants to f...

362
00:22:00,665 --> 00:22:01,540
Ugh.

363
00:22:01,873 --> 00:22:05,290
Look, I'm the only reporter
of my kind here.

364
00:22:05,373 --> 00:22:08,206
If anything happens to me,
you're all getting boycotted.

365
00:22:08,290 --> 00:22:08,915
Alok...

366
00:22:09,498 --> 00:22:10,956
I'll take responsibility of him.

367
00:22:11,331 --> 00:22:12,415
He knows nothing.

368
00:22:15,540 --> 00:22:18,123
Lock him up in the dungeon.

369
00:22:18,498 --> 00:22:19,331
Thank you, sir.

370
00:22:19,748 --> 00:22:20,623
Thank you.

371
00:22:20,998 --> 00:22:21,915
You're right.

372
00:22:22,665 --> 00:22:23,581
Alok...

373
00:22:23,623 --> 00:22:25,373
Hey! Don't touch me! Don't you dare!

374
00:22:25,456 --> 00:22:27,081
I couldn't hear him, but you could, right?

375
00:22:27,165 --> 00:22:28,498
No, come on, guys!

376
00:22:28,915 --> 00:22:30,790
I'm the only son of the Baniya family.

377
00:22:30,873 --> 00:22:33,165
You don't know my father,
he's a bloody rascal.

378
00:22:33,248 --> 00:22:34,706
And a retired income tax officer to boot.

379
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:36,748
He'll charge you penalties
that'll wipe out your retirement fund.

380
00:22:36,831 --> 00:22:37,956
Tadaka, a little help?

381
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:38,873
Please help.

382
00:22:41,581 --> 00:22:42,540
Why are you climbing all these stairs?

383
00:22:42,581 --> 00:22:43,706
Are you planning to throw me down?

384
00:22:43,790 --> 00:22:45,415
- Let me go.
- Why have we brought him here?

385
00:22:45,581 --> 00:22:47,456
- We were ordered to take him to the dungeon.
- Put me down right now.

386
00:22:47,790 --> 00:22:49,415
There's only one being
who gives orders here.

387
00:22:49,498 --> 00:22:50,498
Let's talk, okay?

388
00:22:50,540 --> 00:22:52,581
- He's in there, starving.
- Listen to me.

389
00:22:52,665 --> 00:22:53,873
Let's talk man-to-man.

390
00:22:53,956 --> 00:22:55,165
Stop. Yes. Put me down.

391
00:22:55,248 --> 00:22:56,956
- Very good. Thank you. Thank you.
- Throw him.

392
00:22:57,206 --> 00:22:58,165
Throw him where?

393
00:22:58,290 --> 00:22:59,623
NOOOO!

394
00:22:59,706 --> 00:23:00,956
[Screaming]

395
00:23:01,331 --> 00:23:02,665
Ouch! That hurts!

396
00:23:02,790 --> 00:23:03,623
[Screaming]

397
00:23:03,998 --> 00:23:05,081
Oh shit.

398
00:23:05,456 --> 00:23:06,540
Mummy...

399
00:23:08,290 --> 00:23:09,040
What are you doing?

400
00:23:09,123 --> 00:23:10,540
You can't just dump me here and leave!

401
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:11,581
Hello?

402
00:23:11,706 --> 00:23:12,665
It's dark in here.

403
00:23:12,748 --> 00:23:14,206
I'm scared of the dark, bro.

404
00:23:14,748 --> 00:23:16,123
I get panic attacks.

405
00:23:16,206 --> 00:23:17,081
I have anxiety issues.

406
00:23:17,165 --> 00:23:18,831
Darkness triggers my childhood trauma.

407
00:23:18,915 --> 00:23:20,165
Get me out of here!

408
00:23:20,831 --> 00:23:21,873
Hello?

409
00:23:23,373 --> 00:23:24,290
[Breathing Heavily]

410
00:23:24,373 --> 00:23:25,581
Where did they go?

411
00:23:26,206 --> 00:23:27,206
What is this place?

412
00:23:27,956 --> 00:23:29,123
[Breathing Heavily]

413
00:23:40,540 --> 00:23:41,790
Mom always insisted

414
00:23:43,623 --> 00:23:45,581
I memorize the Hanuman Chalisa,
but I never did.

415
00:23:47,248 --> 00:23:48,498
Now I'm paying the price.

416
00:23:49,248 --> 00:23:51,623
O dear lord, I earnestly pray,
please keep the evil away.

417
00:23:51,706 --> 00:23:54,206
O dear lord, I earnestly pray,
please keep the evil away.

418
00:23:56,165 --> 00:23:58,331
- [bats squeaking]
- [Screaming]

419
00:23:59,290 --> 00:24:00,498
[panting]

420
00:24:04,623 --> 00:24:05,873
[metal clanking]

421
00:24:20,540 --> 00:24:21,540
[growling]

422
00:24:21,623 --> 00:24:22,623
[Screaming]

423
00:24:25,665 --> 00:24:26,540
I can hear...?

424
00:24:27,415 --> 00:24:28,665
Now you show up, my dear,

425
00:24:29,165 --> 00:24:33,623
These longing teeth have waited years.

426
00:24:34,623 --> 00:24:36,956
You mean "these longing eyes", right?

427
00:24:37,123 --> 00:24:39,290
Eyes get blamed for no reason.

428
00:24:39,456 --> 00:24:41,665
It's the teeth that enjoy the real fun.

429
00:24:41,748 --> 00:24:42,915
- Teeth?
- Yes.

430
00:24:43,415 --> 00:24:44,456
Who are you anyway?

431
00:24:46,248 --> 00:24:48,665
A wretched soul, much like you,

432
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:52,248
Bound in chains for decades through.

433
00:24:52,998 --> 00:24:55,498
Sir, I'm terrified in here
and you're recounting poetry?

434
00:24:55,581 --> 00:24:56,706
You've only been here a minute,

435
00:24:56,790 --> 00:24:58,540
I've spent decades in this cave.

436
00:24:58,581 --> 00:25:00,498
What more can you expect from a prisoner?

437
00:25:00,581 --> 00:25:01,540
[metal clanking]

438
00:25:01,706 --> 00:25:03,706
But why keep you prisoner?

439
00:25:03,790 --> 00:25:05,415
Why not?
Why can't they hold me prisoner?

440
00:25:05,498 --> 00:25:06,956
Of course they can, you totally qualify.

441
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,165
What's wrong with me?

442
00:25:08,248 --> 00:25:10,415
You've got everything it takes, sir.

443
00:25:10,498 --> 00:25:12,331
You're totally qualified to be a prisoner.

444
00:25:12,706 --> 00:25:13,581
- Right?
- Right.

445
00:25:13,706 --> 00:25:16,206
[exhales heavily]

446
00:25:16,498 --> 00:25:17,540
[growling]

447
00:25:17,623 --> 00:25:19,998
[evil laughter]

448
00:25:21,456 --> 00:25:23,290
Relax mate, relax.

449
00:25:23,623 --> 00:25:24,665
It's alright.

450
00:25:24,790 --> 00:25:25,706
I was just joking.

451
00:25:25,790 --> 00:25:26,665
Oh my god!

452
00:25:26,998 --> 00:25:28,165
Sir, you know English?

453
00:25:28,623 --> 00:25:33,040
I've drunk the blood of enough Englishmen
to pick up their tongue!

454
00:25:33,331 --> 00:25:34,623
Ben Stokes!

455
00:25:35,831 --> 00:25:36,956
Who's Ben Stokes?

456
00:25:37,415 --> 00:25:38,373
An Englishman.

457
00:25:38,456 --> 00:25:39,331
[tongue click]

458
00:25:39,540 --> 00:25:40,915
An Englishman, you say?

459
00:25:42,498 --> 00:25:43,540
An Englishman!

460
00:25:43,998 --> 00:25:45,623
An Englishman!

461
00:25:45,706 --> 00:25:47,373
Oh, those glory days...

462
00:25:47,456 --> 00:25:48,748
[evil laughter]

463
00:25:48,831 --> 00:25:51,373
Thamma! Thamma! Thamma! Thamma!

464
00:25:52,331 --> 00:25:53,540
Blood of Englishmen?

465
00:25:53,873 --> 00:25:54,665
You were a freedom fighter?

466
00:25:55,290 --> 00:25:56,665
You were a revolutionary?

467
00:25:57,123 --> 00:25:58,790
Of course, I was a revolutionary.

468
00:25:59,456 --> 00:26:00,290
Wow.

469
00:26:00,748 --> 00:26:01,706
Come here now.

470
00:26:02,706 --> 00:26:04,290
Give me your blood,

471
00:26:05,206 --> 00:26:06,915
and I'll give you a life of indulgence.

472
00:26:07,373 --> 00:26:08,165
Come here...

473
00:26:08,623 --> 00:26:09,790
come closer.

474
00:26:10,206 --> 00:26:11,456
Hurry up.

475
00:26:12,456 --> 00:26:13,498
Come closer.

476
00:26:14,873 --> 00:26:16,040
Come here now.

477
00:26:17,623 --> 00:26:18,915
[Screaming]

478
00:26:19,206 --> 00:26:20,498
Agh...

479
00:26:20,706 --> 00:26:21,706
Tadaka!

480
00:26:22,165 --> 00:26:22,748
Let's go.

481
00:26:26,498 --> 00:26:28,581
[Screaming]

482
00:26:32,331 --> 00:26:33,331
Tadaka!

483
00:26:38,581 --> 00:26:40,331
Veeran, go get them!

484
00:26:42,206 --> 00:26:43,623
[Screaming]

485
00:26:52,956 --> 00:26:53,790
Alok...

486
00:26:54,290 --> 00:26:55,165
come on, let's move.

487
00:26:55,248 --> 00:26:56,206
- No, I can't.
- Get up!

488
00:27:00,956 --> 00:27:01,998
[growling]

489
00:27:03,206 --> 00:27:06,081
[Mystical song]

490
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:15,331
- Easy, easy, easy.
- Alok, close your eyes!

491
00:27:35,081 --> 00:27:36,790
Who are you... the Wonder Girl?

492
00:27:36,873 --> 00:27:37,415
Shh.

493
00:27:37,915 --> 00:27:38,998
[sniffing]

494
00:27:39,665 --> 00:27:40,706
Don't panic.

495
00:27:41,206 --> 00:27:42,831
They won't find us in this dense forest.

496
00:27:43,248 --> 00:27:44,748
They will sniff you out.

497
00:27:45,081 --> 00:27:47,706
What are they, sniffer dogs?

498
00:27:48,956 --> 00:27:50,248
Now they won't be able to...

499
00:27:52,290 --> 00:27:54,040
[Breathing Heavily]

500
00:27:58,581 --> 00:27:59,623
Veeran!

501
00:28:03,290 --> 00:28:05,165
[Romantic music]

502
00:28:26,290 --> 00:28:27,873
- Alok, you see that truck?
- Yeah.

503
00:28:28,331 --> 00:28:29,415
You need to jump from here.

504
00:28:29,581 --> 00:28:30,206
- Okay?
- Me?

505
00:28:30,290 --> 00:28:31,165
- Yes.
- From here?

506
00:28:31,415 --> 00:28:32,998
I've never even thrown a bloody stone
from this height.

507
00:28:33,081 --> 00:28:33,915
How do you expect me to jump
from this height?

508
00:28:33,998 --> 00:28:35,206
- Alok, we don't have time.
- No.

509
00:28:35,290 --> 00:28:36,373
- You have to go.
- Yes.

510
00:28:36,581 --> 00:28:37,665
- Yes.
- What about you?

511
00:28:37,873 --> 00:28:39,248
We're forbidden from going any further.

512
00:28:39,665 --> 00:28:41,456
You saved my life. Not once but twice.

513
00:28:42,165 --> 00:28:44,181
I can't leave you behind.

514
00:28:44,206 --> 00:28:45,373
They'll throw you in that cave.

515
00:28:45,456 --> 00:28:46,581
[Sighs]

516
00:28:47,331 --> 00:28:49,623
Alok, they're almost here.

517
00:28:49,790 --> 00:28:50,415
Go!

518
00:28:50,498 --> 00:28:51,165
Yes.

519
00:28:51,290 --> 00:28:52,748
They'll kill you
and throw me in that cave.

520
00:28:52,831 --> 00:28:53,623
Go, Alok!

521
00:28:53,998 --> 00:28:56,248
[panting]

522
00:28:57,456 --> 00:28:58,373
Hurry.

523
00:29:03,748 --> 00:29:04,748
Go on.

524
00:29:06,748 --> 00:29:07,665
Go.

525
00:29:11,998 --> 00:29:12,998
Hurry.

526
00:29:16,206 --> 00:29:17,123
Look,

527
00:29:17,998 --> 00:29:19,956
I have no intention of dying together.

528
00:29:21,248 --> 00:29:22,415
That leaves us with only one option:

529
00:29:23,748 --> 00:29:25,373
How about
we live together instead, hmm?!

530
00:29:26,748 --> 00:29:28,248
[Sighs]

531
00:29:29,206 --> 00:29:30,831
Once you're fully recovered,

532
00:29:31,373 --> 00:29:32,498
I'll take you home.

533
00:29:34,790 --> 00:29:36,165
[Sombre music]

534
00:29:40,956 --> 00:29:41,748
[Grunts]

535
00:29:44,415 --> 00:29:46,040
[Winces in pain]

536
00:29:48,915 --> 00:29:49,956
Girl, you have no fear!

537
00:29:50,623 --> 00:29:51,998
You should totally go for the Olympics.

538
00:29:52,498 --> 00:29:53,831
You could probably bring home
three or four golds, easy.

539
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:10,040
Though not officially,
still yours I'll forever be.

540
00:30:10,123 --> 00:30:12,706
Yours I'll forever be.

541
00:30:16,956 --> 00:30:18,665
[gentle music]

542
00:30:22,790 --> 00:30:28,790
Though not officially,
still yours I'll forever be.

543
00:30:28,873 --> 00:30:32,706
Yours I'll forever be.

544
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:41,373
Whether or not I am there with you.

545
00:30:46,998 --> 00:30:51,706
Love that no one can understand but you,

546
00:30:51,790 --> 00:30:56,498
Something that's only felt by you.

547
00:30:56,581 --> 00:31:01,331
Something that cannot
be measured or subdued,

548
00:31:01,415 --> 00:31:06,581
Something that even time
can't hold from you.

549
00:31:06,998 --> 00:31:11,248
Love that I have for you,

550
00:31:11,665 --> 00:31:16,081
not just my heart but all of me too.

551
00:31:16,873 --> 00:31:22,123
[Sanskrit Chants]

552
00:31:22,831 --> 00:31:26,831
Sir, Mr. Alok's hit the afterlife!

553
00:31:33,081 --> 00:31:35,540
Now Mr. Alok's entered heaven!

554
00:31:36,248 --> 00:31:36,831
[Sobs]

555
00:31:36,956 --> 00:31:40,748
If you've got that kind of pull up there,
why not just call him back?

556
00:31:40,915 --> 00:31:41,415
Huh?

557
00:31:41,498 --> 00:31:42,331
Mom?

558
00:31:42,831 --> 00:31:43,873
Huh?

559
00:31:48,498 --> 00:31:49,373
Alok...

560
00:31:49,956 --> 00:31:50,790
Alok!

561
00:31:50,873 --> 00:31:51,956
ALOK!!!

562
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:53,665
- My child!
- Mom!

563
00:31:53,790 --> 00:31:55,123
Mom! Mom!

564
00:31:55,206 --> 00:31:56,915
My son's back.

565
00:31:57,081 --> 00:31:59,540
My son is back.

566
00:31:59,623 --> 00:32:00,415
Mom, I'm fine.

567
00:32:00,915 --> 00:32:02,581
My son's back.

568
00:32:02,665 --> 00:32:03,873
Take that off.

569
00:32:04,748 --> 00:32:05,498
Dad!

570
00:32:09,581 --> 00:32:10,331
Oh Dad!

571
00:32:11,748 --> 00:32:14,956
A true influencer, indeed...
an influencer-priest!

572
00:32:16,790 --> 00:32:18,331
Thank God!

573
00:32:18,415 --> 00:32:19,206
Alok!

574
00:32:19,290 --> 00:32:20,331
Alok is alive!

575
00:32:20,415 --> 00:32:21,873
Sudha... Sudha, listen...

576
00:32:21,956 --> 00:32:22,331
Yes.

577
00:32:22,415 --> 00:32:25,373
Something tells me he's not our son.

578
00:32:26,498 --> 00:32:29,831
Sudha, he could be an imposter.

579
00:32:29,915 --> 00:32:32,081
Someone who'll milk this situation later.

580
00:32:32,165 --> 00:32:33,290
You mean he'll take advantage of you?

581
00:32:34,290 --> 00:32:36,623
Even the garbage man

582
00:32:36,706 --> 00:32:38,415
won't pick up your trash
without you begging him to.

583
00:32:38,623 --> 00:32:39,831
Who'd take advantage of you?

584
00:32:40,248 --> 00:32:41,331
- You...
- It's fine, Mom.

585
00:32:42,081 --> 00:32:43,415
Let Dad clear his doubts.

586
00:32:43,831 --> 00:32:44,790
- No way.
- Mom...

587
00:32:44,873 --> 00:32:46,331
This won't take long.

588
00:32:47,915 --> 00:32:49,165
[Sighs]

589
00:32:51,790 --> 00:32:53,206
So you're Alok.

590
00:32:54,415 --> 00:32:55,498
Alok Goyal?

591
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:56,956
Yes, Dad.

592
00:32:58,706 --> 00:33:00,665
We used to have a dog.

593
00:33:01,415 --> 00:33:02,831
What was its name?

594
00:33:03,040 --> 00:33:04,040
Moti.

595
00:33:05,873 --> 00:33:08,206
What percentile did you get
in high school?

596
00:33:09,498 --> 00:33:10,331
56!

597
00:33:10,540 --> 00:33:11,373
Huh?

598
00:33:11,540 --> 00:33:12,248
[laughing]

599
00:33:12,331 --> 00:33:14,540
Okay, fine... 55.6%.

600
00:33:14,748 --> 00:33:15,831
- Yes.
- Dad, can we go outside now and--

601
00:33:15,915 --> 00:33:17,748
Hold on... wait.

602
00:33:18,831 --> 00:33:20,206
Back there...

603
00:33:20,748 --> 00:33:24,498
Uh, you've got a mole on your bum...

604
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:27,956
[unzipping the pants]

605
00:33:28,206 --> 00:33:28,956
Here you go.

606
00:33:29,873 --> 00:33:30,665
Pull your pants up.

607
00:33:31,081 --> 00:33:32,665
I wanted to see the mole,
not your dump hole.

608
00:33:33,123 --> 00:33:34,540
Now cut the drama,

609
00:33:34,623 --> 00:33:36,790
or should I share your internet history
screenshots with Mom?

610
00:33:36,873 --> 00:33:38,498
Hey... MY SON!!!

611
00:33:38,956 --> 00:33:40,831
My Alok... my Goyal!

612
00:33:41,665 --> 00:33:42,540
[Chuckling]

613
00:33:42,665 --> 00:33:43,623
Okay.

614
00:33:46,415 --> 00:33:48,123
Mom, how do you even live with this man?

615
00:33:48,665 --> 00:33:49,998
They say blood recognizes blood.

616
00:33:50,248 --> 00:33:51,290
He can't even do that.

617
00:33:51,415 --> 00:33:52,581
Let it go, son.

618
00:33:52,748 --> 00:33:54,581
This man's blood's negative too.

619
00:34:05,081 --> 00:34:06,290
What's your name, dear?

620
00:34:06,873 --> 00:34:07,706
Tadaka.

621
00:34:08,248 --> 00:34:09,165
Tadaka?

622
00:34:09,998 --> 00:34:11,540
Sounds like a demon's name.

623
00:34:13,206 --> 00:34:16,040
It's Tarika. Her name is Tarika...

624
00:34:16,581 --> 00:34:17,915
She saved my life.

625
00:34:19,081 --> 00:34:21,165
Without her,
it would've been game over for me.

626
00:34:25,498 --> 00:34:28,581
Seems like your "game over"
happened a long time ago.

627
00:34:30,790 --> 00:34:34,123
Mom, Dad, a bear attacked me.

628
00:34:34,415 --> 00:34:35,623
Then she just appeared out of nowhere.

629
00:34:36,790 --> 00:34:38,456
Nursed me back to health.

630
00:34:39,165 --> 00:34:42,123
You didn't just save him,

631
00:34:42,623 --> 00:34:44,248
you saved us too.

632
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:47,081
No, I only saved him.

633
00:34:47,415 --> 00:34:47,998
[Chuckling]

634
00:34:48,123 --> 00:34:49,748
Oh, my innocent Tarika...

635
00:34:51,290 --> 00:34:52,248
Why is she here?

636
00:34:55,873 --> 00:34:56,873
Up in the mountains,

637
00:34:57,790 --> 00:35:00,498
her stepmom and step-uncle

638
00:35:00,790 --> 00:35:03,331
tried forcing her to marry some old creep.

639
00:35:03,623 --> 00:35:04,831
I stopped it.

640
00:35:05,373 --> 00:35:07,790
I said, "Nope,
this wedding's not happening."

641
00:35:08,206 --> 00:35:10,081
Sounds like a movie plot.

642
00:35:10,165 --> 00:35:11,706
It's not a movie plot,
it's a saga of cruelty.

643
00:35:11,873 --> 00:35:12,581
Cruelty?

644
00:35:12,665 --> 00:35:13,665
Yeah, her stepmom's cruelty.

645
00:35:13,831 --> 00:35:15,540
Good call, son.

646
00:35:16,373 --> 00:35:17,540
I'm glad you brought her here.

647
00:35:17,748 --> 00:35:18,831
She stays here now.

648
00:35:19,540 --> 00:35:21,248
Here? Why?

649
00:35:21,415 --> 00:35:22,081
Why you ask?

650
00:35:22,165 --> 00:35:23,665
She saved Alok's life.

651
00:35:23,748 --> 00:35:25,706
Eight years ago you had an accident.

652
00:35:25,873 --> 00:35:26,581
Right.

653
00:35:26,665 --> 00:35:30,415
Did we make the doctor
who saved you stay with us?

654
00:35:30,915 --> 00:35:31,831
End of discussion.

655
00:35:32,290 --> 00:35:33,331
She stays.

656
00:35:33,415 --> 00:35:35,206
She saved him. Full and final.

657
00:35:35,290 --> 00:35:36,623
Come on, let me show you the house.

658
00:35:36,706 --> 00:35:37,873
My son's back.

659
00:35:37,956 --> 00:35:40,248
She saved him.

660
00:35:40,331 --> 00:35:41,123
Just like that...?

661
00:35:46,790 --> 00:35:48,081
Hallelujah! Hallelujah!

662
00:35:48,165 --> 00:35:49,123
What is your name?

663
00:35:49,206 --> 00:35:50,623
[laughing]

664
00:35:50,706 --> 00:35:53,248
The hand of God is with youuu.

665
00:35:53,331 --> 00:35:55,123
Hallelujah! Hallelujah!

666
00:35:55,290 --> 00:35:57,331
HALLELUJAH!

667
00:35:59,998 --> 00:36:01,540
Hallelujah! Hallelujah!

668
00:36:01,623 --> 00:36:02,581
[Clapping]

669
00:36:02,665 --> 00:36:05,040
Hallelujah! Hallelujah!

670
00:36:05,748 --> 00:36:09,165
Danger looms over India!

671
00:36:09,706 --> 00:36:12,373
The enemy's set a beauty trap.

672
00:36:13,123 --> 00:36:14,831
She says "Hi" to ensnare,

673
00:36:15,540 --> 00:36:17,373
then hooks them with a "Love you, dear".

674
00:36:17,956 --> 00:36:20,998
The young men of our country
are falling victim to Honey Traps!

675
00:36:21,706 --> 00:36:22,956
She'll call to you,

676
00:36:23,165 --> 00:36:24,415
but don't go near,

677
00:36:25,540 --> 00:36:26,748
She'll trap your heart,

678
00:36:26,831 --> 00:36:28,540
so don't get caught here.

679
00:36:29,165 --> 00:36:32,206
Love isn't easy, better know that,

680
00:36:32,665 --> 00:36:36,290
It's a trap, and you'll get caught flat.

681
00:36:41,623 --> 00:36:42,915
[eerie music]

682
00:36:43,831 --> 00:36:46,206
Alok, here's your favorite Rajma
(kidney beans).

683
00:36:46,290 --> 00:36:47,123
Wow,

684
00:36:47,206 --> 00:36:48,540
I've been dying to have this.

685
00:36:48,831 --> 00:36:49,915
You didn't take anything.

686
00:36:50,165 --> 00:36:51,040
Here, have this, dear.

687
00:36:51,373 --> 00:36:52,873
Tomorrow I'll make 'chole bathoore'
(fried bread with chickpeas).

688
00:36:53,415 --> 00:36:56,206
I'll make any vegetarian dish you want,
you just have to name it.

689
00:36:56,290 --> 00:36:57,248
She's a great cook.

690
00:36:57,498 --> 00:36:58,790
What would you like?

691
00:36:58,915 --> 00:36:59,790
Barasingha ! (reindeer)

692
00:37:00,040 --> 00:37:01,040
Barasingha ?

693
00:37:02,623 --> 00:37:03,540
Barasingha ?

694
00:37:05,206 --> 00:37:06,123
Singhada ! (Water chestnuts)

695
00:37:06,915 --> 00:37:07,790
Big Singhada ! (Big water chestnuts)

696
00:37:08,248 --> 00:37:09,373
It's their specialty.

697
00:37:09,623 --> 00:37:11,790
They are huge.

698
00:37:13,248 --> 00:37:13,998
[Chuckling]

699
00:37:14,706 --> 00:37:16,873
I wouldn't even mind a rabbit if I--

700
00:37:17,331 --> 00:37:18,998
If she could keep it as a pet!

701
00:37:19,831 --> 00:37:21,040
They raise rabbits.

702
00:37:21,456 --> 00:37:24,165
So, who's in your family besides rabbits?

703
00:37:24,248 --> 00:37:25,331
No one.

704
00:37:25,706 --> 00:37:26,956
What do you mean by "no one"?

705
00:37:27,040 --> 00:37:28,248
No one means no one.

706
00:37:28,706 --> 00:37:30,206
She's a true, pure orphan.

707
00:37:30,915 --> 00:37:33,206
She lost her parents young.

708
00:37:33,331 --> 00:37:34,206
[tongue click]

709
00:37:34,331 --> 00:37:35,956
If her parents died,

710
00:37:36,456 --> 00:37:37,706
How did the stepmom come into the picture?

711
00:37:37,790 --> 00:37:38,831
Stepmom, who?

712
00:37:39,623 --> 00:37:43,040
- The one forcing her to marry?
- [Coughs]

713
00:37:43,206 --> 00:37:43,998
Oh, her!

714
00:37:44,081 --> 00:37:46,915
Yes, her.
So, do you have a stepmom or not?

715
00:37:47,123 --> 00:37:47,831
No.

716
00:37:47,915 --> 00:37:48,415
No?

717
00:37:49,081 --> 00:37:49,456
No?

718
00:37:49,540 --> 00:37:50,081
No.

719
00:37:50,623 --> 00:37:51,456
No,

720
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:53,748
she means she isn't a mother,
she is a witch.

721
00:37:53,956 --> 00:37:56,498
Then where did this witchy-stepmom
come from if her parents were dead?

722
00:37:57,081 --> 00:37:59,165
Come on now,
this isn't the time to ask such things.

723
00:37:59,290 --> 00:38:00,831
It's the right time.
It's just eight o'clock.

724
00:38:01,248 --> 00:38:02,206
- Well where did she come from?--
- Papa!--

725
00:38:02,290 --> 00:38:03,790
Rajma, stepma...

726
00:38:03,998 --> 00:38:04,915
Speak up now.

727
00:38:06,748 --> 00:38:08,456
Come on, tell me,
where did she come from?

728
00:38:10,581 --> 00:38:11,581
- [sneezes]
- [glass shattering]

729
00:38:15,373 --> 00:38:17,081
[eerie music]

730
00:38:20,456 --> 00:38:21,415
[Chuckling]

731
00:38:22,581 --> 00:38:23,831
I'm not hungry.

732
00:38:24,581 --> 00:38:25,498
No problem.

733
00:38:25,581 --> 00:38:26,956
Go rest in your room.

734
00:38:27,456 --> 00:38:28,831
You can have some milk before bed.

735
00:38:31,581 --> 00:38:32,790
[chair creaks]

736
00:38:37,373 --> 00:38:38,290
Sudha...

737
00:38:39,665 --> 00:38:40,706
Something's fishy.

738
00:38:41,456 --> 00:38:42,831
It's a sap trap.

739
00:38:42,915 --> 00:38:43,706
Huh?

740
00:38:43,790 --> 00:38:44,873
Honey trap.

741
00:38:45,165 --> 00:38:46,123
Honey trap.

742
00:38:46,540 --> 00:38:48,456
She says "Hi" to ensnare,

743
00:38:48,540 --> 00:38:50,165
then hooks them with a "Love you, dear".

744
00:38:50,373 --> 00:38:54,040
Mark my words, she'll steal our land
and property one day.

745
00:38:55,373 --> 00:38:56,165
I knew it.

746
00:38:56,248 --> 00:38:56,998
Right?

747
00:38:57,665 --> 00:39:00,081
This is what happens
if you binge on crime shows.

748
00:39:00,581 --> 00:39:04,748
What's a beautiful girl like her doing
with Alok if it's not a honey trap?

749
00:39:05,081 --> 00:39:05,956
What do you mean?

750
00:39:06,040 --> 00:39:09,956
Alok's a goof, an idiot...
he's nothing special.

751
00:39:10,040 --> 00:39:10,956
Shut up!

752
00:39:11,081 --> 00:39:12,415
My son looks like a superstar.

753
00:39:13,081 --> 00:39:14,081
He's taken after my brother.

754
00:39:14,831 --> 00:39:15,831
Gone senile...

755
00:39:15,915 --> 00:39:17,748
[Dog Barking]

756
00:39:24,831 --> 00:39:25,456
[Hissing]

757
00:39:28,540 --> 00:39:29,581
What happened, Tarika?

758
00:39:31,373 --> 00:39:33,206
Is there something wrong with my name?

759
00:39:33,665 --> 00:39:34,956
No... not at all.

760
00:39:35,540 --> 00:39:38,081
Tadaka's just a bit weird for the city,

761
00:39:38,831 --> 00:39:40,373
that's why... Tarika.

762
00:39:41,165 --> 00:39:42,456
Do you know what Tarika means?

763
00:39:44,665 --> 00:39:45,623
A star!

764
00:39:46,915 --> 00:39:47,915
That's exactly what you are.

765
00:39:52,206 --> 00:39:56,290
Your ways, name, food, culture...

766
00:39:56,915 --> 00:39:57,790
everything's different.

767
00:39:57,873 --> 00:39:58,748
You're different.

768
00:39:59,040 --> 00:40:00,081
I understand.

769
00:40:00,665 --> 00:40:01,998
But my parents won't.

770
00:40:02,831 --> 00:40:05,706
That's why I lied to placate them.

771
00:40:05,790 --> 00:40:07,165
We can't lie.

772
00:40:07,373 --> 00:40:08,498
Why not?

773
00:40:09,790 --> 00:40:14,165
A lie that helps someone isn't a lie,
it's the truth.

774
00:40:14,290 --> 00:40:14,998
Truly?

775
00:40:15,081 --> 00:40:15,998
Nope, a lie.

776
00:40:16,206 --> 00:40:17,040
A lie?

777
00:40:17,248 --> 00:40:18,165
I get it.

778
00:40:18,706 --> 00:40:21,040
Your culture forbids lying.

779
00:40:21,790 --> 00:40:23,206
But here, it's a whole different game.

780
00:40:27,873 --> 00:40:28,748
Umm,

781
00:40:29,498 --> 00:40:31,998
I know it's not like your airplane.

782
00:40:32,123 --> 00:40:33,081
It's a little different.

783
00:40:33,956 --> 00:40:34,956
Just adjust for a few days.

784
00:40:35,373 --> 00:40:37,873
And adjust to Mom's clothes for a bit too.

785
00:40:38,206 --> 00:40:40,498
We'll get you new clothes
first thing tomorrow.

786
00:40:40,581 --> 00:40:41,831
[dramatic music]

787
00:40:43,540 --> 00:40:44,415
Tarika?

788
00:40:50,748 --> 00:40:51,956
She was here a second ago.
Where'd she go?

789
00:40:53,623 --> 00:40:54,665
Tarika!

790
00:40:58,915 --> 00:40:59,956
[Knock On Door]

791
00:41:01,331 --> 00:41:02,206
Tarika?

792
00:41:02,498 --> 00:41:03,665
[door creaking]

793
00:41:08,873 --> 00:41:09,915
Tarika... Tadaka!

794
00:41:11,415 --> 00:41:12,290
Tadaka!

795
00:41:14,831 --> 00:41:15,706
Tadaka!

796
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:17,123
[Screaming]

797
00:41:17,206 --> 00:41:18,915
[maniacal laughter]

798
00:41:23,248 --> 00:41:24,248
Shush.

799
00:41:25,373 --> 00:41:26,540
Why are you laughing like that?

800
00:41:27,248 --> 00:41:28,498
It's just how I laugh.

801
00:41:29,206 --> 00:41:29,998
Okay...

802
00:41:30,498 --> 00:41:31,915
But what are you doing under the bed?

803
00:41:36,873 --> 00:41:38,206
I like it here.

804
00:41:41,123 --> 00:41:42,665
Me too.

805
00:41:43,498 --> 00:41:45,540
[thumping heartbeat]

806
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:48,623
I can hear your heart beat.

807
00:41:49,790 --> 00:41:50,915
It's racing.

808
00:41:52,123 --> 00:41:55,540
My heart always races when I'm with you.

809
00:41:56,373 --> 00:41:58,498
[Romantic music]

810
00:42:09,956 --> 00:42:10,915
[Hissing]

811
00:42:14,915 --> 00:42:15,831
Alok!

812
00:42:16,831 --> 00:42:17,748
Alok!

813
00:42:20,581 --> 00:42:21,665
What are you doing down there?

814
00:42:21,748 --> 00:42:23,290
Mom, I was just...

815
00:42:25,831 --> 00:42:27,248
showing Tarika my room.

816
00:42:29,123 --> 00:42:30,081
Fine.

817
00:42:30,165 --> 00:42:31,081
[Sighs]

818
00:42:31,915 --> 00:42:33,665
Give her some milk once you're done.

819
00:42:34,331 --> 00:42:35,206
Hmm?

820
00:42:35,331 --> 00:42:36,206
Yes.

821
00:42:36,831 --> 00:42:37,581
Okay.

822
00:42:37,956 --> 00:42:39,331
My son's all grown up now.

823
00:42:40,331 --> 00:42:41,498
She loves him,

824
00:42:42,456 --> 00:42:43,831
she loves him not.

825
00:42:44,040 --> 00:42:44,748
[metal clanking]

826
00:42:44,831 --> 00:42:45,956
She loves him,

827
00:42:47,290 --> 00:42:48,456
she loves him not.

828
00:42:51,081 --> 00:42:52,873
[Breathing Heavily]

829
00:42:55,956 --> 00:42:58,498
You're a Betaal and he's human...

830
00:43:00,290 --> 00:43:01,540
yet he still escaped?

831
00:43:02,706 --> 00:43:04,331
Shame on you, Veeran.

832
00:43:04,873 --> 00:43:07,165
I can't even show my teeth
to anyone now, thanks to you.

833
00:43:08,873 --> 00:43:10,706
I tried my best to stop him.

834
00:43:11,540 --> 00:43:13,623
But Tadaka ran away with that human.

835
00:43:14,123 --> 00:43:15,373
What now?

836
00:43:16,498 --> 00:43:17,248
I...

837
00:43:18,540 --> 00:43:19,456
I...

838
00:43:20,206 --> 00:43:20,790
I...

839
00:43:20,873 --> 00:43:22,915
What's with all the "I... I... I..."?

840
00:43:24,706 --> 00:43:26,998
You'll keep whining
