00:57:46,956 --> 00:57:48,665
That's a weird habit.

1110
00:57:49,099 --> 00:57:50,890
There are so many drinks in the world,
yet you choose blood!

1111
00:57:50,915 --> 00:57:51,790
Why are you doing this?

1112
00:57:52,081 --> 00:57:53,331
- Alok...
- No, no, no, stay back.

1113
00:57:53,415 --> 00:57:54,748
You relishing a barasingha
is still something I can relate to.

1114
00:57:55,123 --> 00:57:56,623
People have exotic taste buds.

1115
00:57:56,790 --> 00:57:57,790
They eat anything...

1116
00:57:58,123 --> 00:57:59,831
dogs, cats, jackal or even bats.

1117
00:57:59,915 --> 00:58:01,540
But who drink blood, dude?!

1118
00:58:01,956 --> 00:58:02,873
Alok...

1119
00:58:03,873 --> 00:58:06,498
Wait a second... Are you a vampire?

1120
00:58:06,790 --> 00:58:07,748
Vampire?

1121
00:58:07,998 --> 00:58:09,956
Like in those horror movies?

1122
00:58:10,040 --> 00:58:11,206
They drink blood,

1123
00:58:11,456 --> 00:58:14,165
get burned by sunlight, sleep in coffins,
and have no shadows.

1124
00:58:14,248 --> 00:58:15,081
Close cousins of ghosts?

1125
00:58:15,623 --> 00:58:16,915
Invisible in mirrors.

1126
00:58:19,956 --> 00:58:20,873
I can see you.

1127
00:58:21,081 --> 00:58:22,040
Are you a hybrid?

1128
00:58:22,206 --> 00:58:22,790
Alok...

1129
00:58:22,873 --> 00:58:23,956
- Stop right there.
- We are Betaals.

1130
00:58:24,915 --> 00:58:25,998
We are Betaals.

1131
00:58:26,331 --> 00:58:28,373
We only drink blood.

1132
00:58:28,456 --> 00:58:29,748
"We ONLY drink blood."

1133
00:58:29,915 --> 00:58:30,790
What a claim!

1134
00:58:31,248 --> 00:58:32,081
- Alok...
- No!

1135
00:58:32,165 --> 00:58:33,415
Don't come closer, I'll smash you.

1136
00:58:35,081 --> 00:58:37,206
How would I even explain
to the world who and what you are?

1137
00:58:37,915 --> 00:58:39,998
Tomorrow at dinner when Mom asks
what Tarika wants... what will I say?

1138
00:58:40,165 --> 00:58:41,998
"Nothing, Mom,
just give her some fresh blood!"

1139
00:58:42,498 --> 00:58:43,956
Only the veteran actor Dharmendra
has the right to say,

1140
00:58:44,040 --> 00:58:45,706
"I'll drink your blood, you dog."

1141
00:58:46,206 --> 00:58:48,581
He too just says it,
never actually drinks it.

1142
00:58:51,498 --> 00:58:52,373
SHIT!!!

1143
00:58:52,956 --> 00:58:54,206
Here I thought you were a Wonder Girl,

1144
00:58:54,748 --> 00:58:55,915
turns out you're Dracula.

1145
00:58:56,331 --> 00:58:57,331
Dracula?

1146
00:58:57,665 --> 00:58:58,540
Who's that?

1147
00:58:58,748 --> 00:58:59,873
You don't know who Dracula is?

1148
00:58:59,956 --> 00:59:03,665
Collar up, fangs out, walks like this.

1149
00:59:03,873 --> 00:59:06,290
I mean...
He's got to be related to you somehow.

1150
00:59:06,498 --> 00:59:08,706
You might not know him.
Maybe he's one of your uncles.

1151
00:59:09,373 --> 00:59:13,040
Alok, we don't drink human blood anymore.

1152
00:59:13,540 --> 00:59:14,623
Why should I believe you?

1153
00:59:15,331 --> 00:59:16,040
Why?

1154
00:59:16,165 --> 00:59:17,915
Isn't it enough that I said we don't?

1155
00:59:19,373 --> 00:59:20,290
I don't know.

1156
00:59:21,040 --> 00:59:23,290
We used to drink human blood...

1157
00:59:24,081 --> 00:59:26,956
but only of those less human, more beasts.

1158
00:59:28,540 --> 00:59:32,790
But after 1947, things changed.

1159
00:59:34,206 --> 00:59:35,165
What do you mean?

1160
00:59:36,206 --> 00:59:37,998
[Screaming]

1161
00:59:38,831 --> 00:59:40,040
[glass shattering]

1162
00:59:40,998 --> 00:59:42,665
[Screaming]

1163
00:59:43,665 --> 00:59:45,040
Riots broke out.

1164
00:59:46,081 --> 00:59:49,123
Rioters were rolling into town,
packed into trains.

1165
00:59:51,165 --> 00:59:52,748
[people wailing]

1166
00:59:54,873 --> 01:00:00,123
We went there to drink the killers' blood
and save the innocent.

1167
01:00:03,456 --> 01:00:06,873
But when we arrived, we were stunned.

1168
01:00:08,040 --> 01:00:10,706
There weren't rioters,
just innocent people

1169
01:00:11,373 --> 01:00:14,706
who'd slaughtered each other,
and were lying dead.

1170
01:00:15,415 --> 01:00:19,956
We'd never seen that much blood.

1171
01:00:20,956 --> 01:00:27,331
No other animal kills like that
for no reason.

1172
01:00:28,790 --> 01:00:31,081
From that day, we decided

1173
01:00:31,956 --> 01:00:33,873
humans are poisonous

1174
01:00:35,373 --> 01:00:37,706
because their blood is toxic.

1175
01:00:38,581 --> 01:00:40,873
So we stopped drinking their blood.

1176
01:00:43,498 --> 01:00:45,040
[blood dripping]

1177
01:00:45,748 --> 01:00:47,540
[Gasping]

1178
01:00:53,415 --> 01:00:54,498
You are lying.

1179
01:00:55,165 --> 01:00:56,998
Back in that cave, that poet...

1180
01:00:57,706 --> 01:00:58,831
he wanted to drink my blood.

1181
01:00:59,331 --> 01:01:03,123
That's why we locked him
in the cursed mountain.

1182
01:01:03,915 --> 01:01:04,831
Who is he?

1183
01:01:05,706 --> 01:01:07,248
The most powerful,

1184
01:01:07,748 --> 01:01:09,081
deadliest of us all...

1185
01:01:09,706 --> 01:01:10,540
Yakshashan.

1186
01:01:11,498 --> 01:01:13,706
Our ancestor.

1187
01:01:15,373 --> 01:01:17,915
The one who made us Betaals.

1188
01:01:18,956 --> 01:01:20,040
Our hero...

1189
01:01:21,290 --> 01:01:22,290
our Thamma.

1190
01:01:22,748 --> 01:01:24,165
[dramatic music]

1191
01:01:24,831 --> 01:01:25,706
[growling]

1192
01:01:25,790 --> 01:01:29,040
We all agreed not to drink human blood,

1193
01:01:30,956 --> 01:01:33,706
but Yakshashan refused.

1194
01:01:34,998 --> 01:01:37,498
[evil laughter]

1195
01:01:42,081 --> 01:01:43,373
[growling]

1196
01:01:43,498 --> 01:01:44,706
You broke the rule.

1197
01:01:45,665 --> 01:01:46,790
You will be punished.

1198
01:01:49,415 --> 01:01:50,498
Your rules are baseless.

1199
01:01:51,040 --> 01:01:53,040
Drinking human blood is in our nature.

1200
01:01:53,706 --> 01:01:56,790
One day, we'll turn them all
and rule the world.

1201
01:01:56,873 --> 01:01:57,706
We will rule!

1202
01:01:57,998 --> 01:02:01,831
We want to break free
from this curse of drinking blood.

1203
01:02:02,665 --> 01:02:03,456
[metal clanking]

1204
01:02:03,540 --> 01:02:04,706
You're our ancestor.

1205
01:02:05,915 --> 01:02:07,081
You created us.

1206
01:02:07,165 --> 01:02:10,998
That's why we keep offering
animal sacrifices to keep you alive.

1207
01:02:11,081 --> 01:02:12,748
From now on,

1208
01:02:13,706 --> 01:02:16,373
you'll stay imprisoned in this cave.

1209
01:02:16,456 --> 01:02:18,123
For how long do you think
you can keep me imprisoned?

1210
01:02:18,206 --> 01:02:19,331
Hundred years of toil and pain,

1211
01:02:19,415 --> 01:02:21,915
The day one of you breaks the rule

1212
01:02:21,998 --> 01:02:23,706
and turns a human into a Betaal...

1213
01:02:23,790 --> 01:02:25,998
I'll be free.

1214
01:02:26,081 --> 01:02:27,748
FREE!!!

1215
01:02:28,540 --> 01:02:30,456
FREE!!!

1216
01:02:32,665 --> 01:02:35,915
You said you imprisoned Yakshashan
after the 1947 incident.

1217
01:02:37,706 --> 01:02:38,706
You were there?

1218
01:02:40,248 --> 01:02:41,498
I mean... How?

1219
01:02:45,748 --> 01:02:46,956
I'm not human.

1220
01:02:48,456 --> 01:02:50,373
I don't have a heartbeat.

1221
01:02:54,581 --> 01:02:56,665
But you do.

1222
01:02:57,081 --> 01:02:58,915
[thumping heartbeat]

1223
01:02:59,206 --> 01:03:02,248
And that's what pulls me to you.

1224
01:03:05,040 --> 01:03:06,581
It just... compels me.

1225
01:03:07,873 --> 01:03:09,498
[doorbell rings]

1226
01:03:11,331 --> 01:03:12,665
[Dog Barking]

1227
01:03:12,873 --> 01:03:13,915
[Door Opens]

1228
01:03:17,373 --> 01:03:18,206
Who are you?

1229
01:03:18,790 --> 01:03:19,956
Inspector P.K. Yadav.

1230
01:03:20,706 --> 01:03:21,790
Oh. Goyal.

1231
01:03:26,123 --> 01:03:27,040
Hello.

1232
01:03:28,665 --> 01:03:30,415
All good, Officer?

1233
01:03:32,248 --> 01:03:33,706
No Mr. Goyal,
I'm afraid things aren't looking good.

1234
01:03:33,790 --> 01:03:35,706
Oh, so you are here seeking a donation?

1235
01:03:36,623 --> 01:03:38,623
Do I look like the one
who'd seek a donation?

1236
01:03:40,206 --> 01:03:41,956
I'm here to investigate.

1237
01:03:42,415 --> 01:03:43,290
Investigate what?

1238
01:03:43,581 --> 01:03:45,290
Something happened with a couple of boys.

1239
01:03:47,790 --> 01:03:48,956
Do you know anything about it?

1240
01:03:49,373 --> 01:03:50,331
No.

1241
01:03:50,790 --> 01:03:52,290
If I did, I'd tell you.

1242
01:03:53,040 --> 01:03:54,456
I'd do anything for the police.

1243
01:03:54,831 --> 01:03:55,790
- Really?
- Yeah.

1244
01:03:56,081 --> 01:03:57,331
Okay, so what have you done
for the police?

1245
01:03:57,665 --> 01:03:59,123
I've watched Singham eight times.

1246
01:03:59,665 --> 01:04:00,540
Big fan.

1247
01:04:01,165 --> 01:04:02,040
Big fan, sir.

1248
01:04:04,456 --> 01:04:05,873
[Tense music]

1249
01:04:20,956 --> 01:04:21,831
What's your name?

1250
01:04:23,373 --> 01:04:23,998
Tarika.

1251
01:04:24,248 --> 01:04:24,998
Tadaka.

1252
01:04:29,165 --> 01:04:30,665
Tadaka or Tarika?

1253
01:04:31,498 --> 01:04:32,373
Only Tarika.

1254
01:04:34,998 --> 01:04:38,040
So, Ms. "Only Tarika,"
were you at a party earlier?

1255
01:04:39,831 --> 01:04:40,498
Hmm?

1256
01:04:40,581 --> 01:04:41,165
Yes.

1257
01:04:41,248 --> 01:04:42,290
Hmm.

1258
01:04:42,915 --> 01:04:44,790
Did some guys misbehave with you there?

1259
01:04:45,331 --> 01:04:46,456
Did they cause trouble?

1260
01:04:47,081 --> 01:04:50,373
That's what I want to discuss...
in private.

1261
01:04:52,040 --> 01:04:52,915
Let's go.

1262
01:04:58,831 --> 01:04:59,873
[Door Closes]

1263
01:05:00,331 --> 01:05:01,248
[fabric rustling]

1264
01:05:08,956 --> 01:05:10,540
Rakhtrambha ! (I'll protect through blood!)

1265
01:05:10,623 --> 01:05:13,081
Sasakhtrambha !
(I'll protect through strength!)

1266
01:05:14,415 --> 01:05:15,290
[Hissing]

1267
01:05:16,665 --> 01:05:17,623
You...?!

1268
01:05:17,873 --> 01:05:18,831
You too?

1269
01:05:20,040 --> 01:05:21,040
Me too.

1270
01:05:22,623 --> 01:05:23,623
Knew it...

1271
01:05:24,915 --> 01:05:27,998
knew who you were the second
I saw those guys.

1272
01:05:31,748 --> 01:05:32,831
Why did you kill them?

1273
01:05:33,998 --> 01:05:34,998
Kill them?

1274
01:05:38,165 --> 01:05:39,290
You killed them, right?

1275
01:05:39,998 --> 01:05:40,915
Hmm?

1276
01:05:45,081 --> 01:05:47,165
Good thing you just broke their necks.

1277
01:05:48,540 --> 01:05:52,581
Biting them and drinking blood
would've been caused a lot of trouble.

1278
01:05:53,456 --> 01:05:54,498
Where did you come from?

1279
01:05:54,831 --> 01:05:56,290
Why did you kill them?

1280
01:05:56,623 --> 01:05:57,581
They...

1281
01:05:58,040 --> 01:06:00,956
they were hurting Alok.

1282
01:06:01,998 --> 01:06:03,373
My head was spinning.

1283
01:06:04,331 --> 01:06:06,790
I lost control.

1284
01:06:07,581 --> 01:06:10,956
I can't remember what happened next.

1285
01:06:11,998 --> 01:06:14,915
For 172 years,
it has been my responsibility,

1286
01:06:15,540 --> 01:06:18,331
to maintain the equilibrium
between humans and our kind.

1287
01:06:19,581 --> 01:06:22,331
And you're messing up that balance.

1288
01:06:23,206 --> 01:06:25,706
Alok's making you lose control.

1289
01:06:26,456 --> 01:06:29,331
You could hurt him and his family.

1290
01:06:29,831 --> 01:06:32,581
You could attack them,
bite them, drink their blood.

1291
01:06:32,956 --> 01:06:35,706
You should leave
before you cause more trouble.

1292
01:06:37,081 --> 01:06:37,956
GO.

1293
01:06:38,040 --> 01:06:39,873
[growling]

1294
01:06:45,290 --> 01:06:46,206
Congratulations, son.

1295
01:06:46,540 --> 01:06:47,415
She finally got caught.

1296
01:06:47,790 --> 01:06:48,915
Come on, Dad.

1297
01:06:48,998 --> 01:06:49,581
[Door Opens]

1298
01:06:50,790 --> 01:06:51,748
All okay, dear?

1299
01:06:52,331 --> 01:06:53,165
Tarika?

1300
01:06:53,540 --> 01:06:54,956
So... what happened?

1301
01:06:57,415 --> 01:06:58,748
[suspense music]

1302
01:06:58,998 --> 01:07:00,290
Why aren't you saying anything?

1303
01:07:00,706 --> 01:07:01,998
I have to leave, Alok.

1304
01:07:02,331 --> 01:07:03,415
What did the officer say?

1305
01:07:03,498 --> 01:07:04,998
Don't worry, whatever it is,
I'll handle it.

1306
01:07:05,415 --> 01:07:09,040
He knows what I did to those guys.

1307
01:07:09,498 --> 01:07:10,873
What did you do?
What exactly does he know?

1308
01:07:11,873 --> 01:07:14,331
The police found their bodies.

1309
01:07:14,998 --> 01:07:16,206
Did you kill them?

1310
01:07:16,665 --> 01:07:17,415
I don't know.

1311
01:07:17,956 --> 01:07:18,956
What do you mean by "you don't know"?

1312
01:07:19,456 --> 01:07:23,331
All I know is you might be
in danger because of me.

1313
01:07:23,415 --> 01:07:24,498
You said you don't drink human blood--

1314
01:07:24,581 --> 01:07:26,040
I'm a Betaal, Alok!

1315
01:07:26,873 --> 01:07:31,623
What if I lose control one day
and hurt you?

1316
01:07:33,623 --> 01:07:35,206
[Breathing Heavily]

1317
01:07:35,831 --> 01:07:37,665
[intense music]

1318
01:07:45,165 --> 01:07:49,040
Whether or not I am there with you.

1319
01:07:49,373 --> 01:07:51,081
[thumping heartbeat]

1320
01:07:51,248 --> 01:07:53,165
I want to be with you...

1321
01:07:55,706 --> 01:07:57,456
but I just can't.

1322
01:08:01,290 --> 01:08:03,373
Our worlds are too different.

1323
01:08:06,706 --> 01:08:07,373
I have to go.

1324
01:08:07,456 --> 01:08:08,706
Please, don't leave.

1325
01:08:08,790 --> 01:08:10,956
[Hissing]

1326
01:08:12,415 --> 01:08:15,040
[intense music]

1327
01:08:31,165 --> 01:08:35,415
What more could I want than you

1328
01:08:35,498 --> 01:08:44,290
remembering me your whole life through,

1329
01:08:44,873 --> 01:08:49,831
Whether or not I am there with you.

1330
01:08:49,956 --> 01:08:54,373
Whether or not I am there with you.

1331
01:08:54,665 --> 01:08:58,873
Even without being beside you,

1332
01:08:58,956 --> 01:09:07,956
Each day, each moment,
I'll still be with you,

1333
01:09:08,456 --> 01:09:13,081
Whether or not I am there with you.

1334
01:09:13,248 --> 01:09:17,290
Whether or not I am there with you.

1335
01:09:17,373 --> 01:09:21,581
I am not away from you,

1336
01:09:22,123 --> 01:09:26,706
I'm right there where you are too.

1337
01:09:26,790 --> 01:09:31,248
I am not away from you,

1338
01:09:31,540 --> 01:09:35,915
I'm right there where you are too.

1339
01:09:46,040 --> 01:09:50,373
I'll always flourish in you,

1340
01:09:50,998 --> 01:09:55,623
Whether or not I am there with you.

1341
01:09:55,706 --> 01:10:00,706
Whether or not I am there with you.

1342
01:10:03,665 --> 01:10:05,956
[car screeching]

1343
01:10:15,373 --> 01:10:17,248
[car horn blaring]

1344
01:10:27,206 --> 01:10:29,123
Tarika, please don't go.

1345
01:10:29,956 --> 01:10:31,248
I don't want to lose you.

1346
01:10:31,706 --> 01:10:33,123
Tarika, please stay.

1347
01:10:34,748 --> 01:10:35,915
Please don't go.

1348
01:10:38,331 --> 01:10:39,415
Stop the bus.

1349
01:10:40,665 --> 01:10:41,915
[bus horn blaring]

1350
01:10:42,623 --> 01:10:43,998
[Tire Screeching]

1351
01:10:45,206 --> 01:10:46,373
[Gasping]

1352
01:10:48,456 --> 01:10:50,498
[car crash]

1353
01:10:54,290 --> 01:10:55,998
[Winces in pain]

1354
01:10:56,081 --> 01:10:57,456
[fire crackling]

1355
01:11:04,456 --> 01:11:05,831
[grunting]

1356
01:11:17,623 --> 01:11:18,581
Alok!

1357
01:11:18,665 --> 01:11:19,915
Alok!

1358
01:11:19,998 --> 01:11:22,456
[Breathing Heavily]

1359
01:11:24,498 --> 01:11:25,456
Alok!

1360
01:11:30,540 --> 01:11:34,498
What more could I want than you

1361
01:11:34,581 --> 01:11:44,665
- remembering me your whole life through,
- Alok...

1362
01:11:45,165 --> 01:11:50,665
Whether or not I am there with you.

1363
01:11:50,748 --> 01:11:54,956
- Whether or not I am there with you.
- [Screaming]

1364
01:11:55,040 --> 01:11:58,915
Whether or not I am there with you.

1365
01:12:00,094 --> 01:12:01,302
[Ambulance Siren]

1366
01:12:03,510 --> 01:12:04,469
Quick! Quick! Right!

1367
01:12:05,094 --> 01:12:06,260
[Phone Ringing]

1368
01:12:07,802 --> 01:12:09,135
Sorry, ma'am, you can't come inside.

1369
01:12:12,510 --> 01:12:14,302
[suspense music]

1370
01:12:25,635 --> 01:12:27,177
This way. Tarika!

1371
01:12:27,260 --> 01:12:28,177
Tarika!

1372
01:12:28,510 --> 01:12:29,385
Where is Alok?

1373
01:12:29,469 --> 01:12:30,135
Where is Alok?

1374
01:12:30,219 --> 01:12:31,677
WHERE IS ALOK?!!!

1375
01:12:31,969 --> 01:12:33,177
[defibrillator charging]

1376
01:12:33,260 --> 01:12:34,594
[electric jolt]

1377
01:12:41,177 --> 01:12:42,719
[flatline tone]

1378
01:12:46,094 --> 01:12:47,844
[Footsteps]

1379
01:12:49,302 --> 01:12:51,260
Doctor, Alok...?

1380
01:12:53,177 --> 01:12:54,177
I'm sorry.

1381
01:13:03,677 --> 01:13:05,052
Sudha...

1382
01:13:05,552 --> 01:13:06,885
[Crying]

1383
01:13:31,302 --> 01:13:32,844
[bats screeching]

1384
01:13:46,010 --> 01:13:47,635
[growling]

1385
01:13:52,010 --> 01:13:53,760
[bats squeaking]

1386
01:14:01,969 --> 01:14:04,677
[Gibberish]

1387
01:14:09,344 --> 01:14:11,010
[dramatic music]

1388
01:14:18,719 --> 01:14:20,052
[growling]

1389
01:14:20,302 --> 01:14:26,552
[Mystical song]

1390
01:14:31,677 --> 01:14:32,969
[evil laughter]

1391
01:14:33,052 --> 01:14:35,427
FREEDOOM!

1392
01:14:40,177 --> 01:14:41,469
The patient's not in the room.

1393
01:14:41,719 --> 01:14:42,635
He's not?

1394
01:14:44,177 --> 01:14:45,177
[Door Opens]

1395
01:14:45,260 --> 01:14:46,135
Alok...?

1396
01:14:51,385 --> 01:14:52,469
Alok!

1397
01:14:54,552 --> 01:14:56,010
Where's Alok?

1398
01:14:57,552 --> 01:14:58,719
[fabric rustling]

1399
01:15:04,927 --> 01:15:05,760
Alok!

1400
01:15:06,802 --> 01:15:07,844
[Door Opens]

1401
01:15:10,635 --> 01:15:12,135
[suspense music]

1402
01:15:21,177 --> 01:15:23,094
[music builds up]

1403
01:15:26,885 --> 01:15:28,427
[glass shattering]

1404
01:15:31,719 --> 01:15:32,760
[Door Opens]

1405
01:15:34,260 --> 01:15:36,385
[dramatic music]

1406
01:15:46,719 --> 01:15:48,427
[slurping]

1407
01:15:52,594 --> 01:15:54,302
[Tense music]

1408
01:16:08,219 --> 01:16:09,594
[Hissing]

1409
01:16:21,177 --> 01:16:22,010
[growling]

1410
01:16:22,094 --> 01:16:23,135
ALOKKK!!!

1411
01:16:23,635 --> 01:16:25,260
[Gasping]

1412
01:16:25,802 --> 01:16:26,760
What's wrong?

1413
01:16:27,135 --> 01:16:28,219
Are you alright?

1414
01:16:32,469 --> 01:16:33,344
Aa...

1415
01:16:33,635 --> 01:16:34,177
Where's Alok?

1416
01:16:34,260 --> 01:16:36,135
He's fine, Alok is fine.

1417
01:16:36,260 --> 01:16:37,927
He's been discharged.
He's sleeping in his room.

1418
01:16:38,010 --> 01:16:40,635
I saw him at the hospital.

1419
01:16:40,719 --> 01:16:42,927
Good you found him.

1420
01:16:43,344 --> 01:16:47,385
Alok woke up and somehow
went upstairs by mistake.

1421
01:16:47,885 --> 01:16:49,010
He got upstairs by mistake?

1422
01:16:49,094 --> 01:16:49,719
Yes.

1423
01:16:49,969 --> 01:16:51,385
Then he ended up
in the blood bank by mistake?

1424
01:16:51,510 --> 01:16:52,260
Yes.

1425
01:16:52,344 --> 01:16:54,302
Who makes such detailed mistakes, huh?

1426
01:16:54,885 --> 01:16:56,052
What about the teeth?

1427
01:16:56,135 --> 01:16:56,635
What teeth?

1428
01:16:56,719 --> 01:16:57,552
Alok's teeth!

1429
01:16:57,760 --> 01:16:59,177
Which teeth? Whose teeth? What--

1430
01:16:59,260 --> 01:17:01,219
He tried to attack his own father!

1431
01:17:01,302 --> 01:17:01,719
Huh?

1432
01:17:01,802 --> 01:17:03,010
[Gibberish]

1433
01:17:03,094 --> 01:17:04,510
The doctor said

1434
01:17:04,802 --> 01:17:07,385
you might be delusional after
your head injury

1435
01:17:07,594 --> 01:17:09,177
and say strange things.

1436
01:17:10,052 --> 01:17:11,094
You should rest.

1437
01:17:11,844 --> 01:17:13,094
There's nothing to be afraid of.

1438
01:17:22,552 --> 01:17:23,969
[Grunts]

1439
01:17:37,010 --> 01:17:38,635
[clock ticking]

1440
01:17:43,052 --> 01:17:45,552
[dramatic music]

1441
01:18:03,552 --> 01:18:04,802
Tadaka, what's wrong with me?

1442
01:18:05,385 --> 01:18:06,694
I acted strangely
at the hospital yesterday.

1443
01:18:06,719 --> 01:18:07,719
Today, I feel weird.

1444
01:18:07,802 --> 01:18:10,552
I can't feel my pulse or heartbeat.

1445
01:18:16,594 --> 01:18:18,385
Rakhtrambha ! (I'll protect through blood!)

1446
01:18:18,469 --> 01:18:21,010
Sasakhtrambha !
(I'll protect through strength!)

1447
01:18:25,844 --> 01:18:27,052
[Breathing Heavily]

1448
01:18:27,219 --> 01:18:28,135
Huh?

1449
01:18:29,719 --> 01:18:30,844
[Grunts]

1450
01:18:37,760 --> 01:18:39,635
[Crying]

1451
01:18:44,052 --> 01:18:45,135
[Sighs]

1452
01:18:50,844 --> 01:18:51,635
[Sobs]

1453
01:18:54,385 --> 01:18:56,802
You turned me?

1454
01:18:58,594 --> 01:18:59,427
So I'm dead now?

1455
01:19:00,760 --> 01:19:01,844
I'm not human anymore?

1456
01:19:03,719 --> 01:19:04,552
Shit!

1457
01:19:05,052 --> 01:19:06,594
Shit! Shit! Shit!

1458
01:19:06,677 --> 01:19:07,427
What do I even do now?

1459
01:19:07,510 --> 01:19:10,302
My life, dreams, ambitions...
it's all over now.

1460
01:19:10,469 --> 01:19:12,302
How do I even face social media?

1461
01:19:12,927 --> 01:19:15,052
How will I ever enjoy Rajma-chawal
(kidney beans with rice) again?

1462
01:19:15,427 --> 01:19:17,677
Guess there goes my life insurance too.

1463
01:19:18,302 --> 01:19:19,302
Why did you do this?

1464
01:19:19,385 --> 01:19:21,510
You would be dead if I didn't, Alok.

1465
01:19:21,594 --> 01:19:25,760
Killing me and then saying I would
be dead otherwise makes zero sense!

1466
01:19:26,094 --> 01:19:27,510
You were so quick to preach back then...

1467
01:19:27,594 --> 01:19:29,302
Humans are this, humans are that.

1468
01:19:29,385 --> 01:19:30,802
They have hatred in their blood.

1469
01:19:30,885 --> 01:19:31,885
Humans are poisonous.

1470
01:19:31,969 --> 01:19:33,052
They are like cloves, garlic and what not.

1471
01:19:33,135 --> 01:19:33,760
What was that about?

1472
01:19:33,844 --> 01:19:35,052
And what about your rules?

1473
01:19:35,135 --> 01:19:37,052
You said you cannot bite humans.

1474
01:19:37,135 --> 01:19:39,094
So why did you bite me?

1475
01:19:39,802 --> 01:19:41,594
[Romantic music]

1476
01:19:52,552 --> 01:19:55,469
Whether or not I am there with you.

1477
01:19:55,635 --> 01:19:57,510
You were dying, Alok...

1478
01:19:58,260 --> 01:20:00,219
I didn't want to lose you.

1479
01:20:04,094 --> 01:20:09,135
Love that no one can understand but you,

1480
01:20:09,219 --> 01:20:13,719
Something that's only felt by through you.

1481
01:20:13,802 --> 01:20:18,510
Something that cannot
be measured or subdued,

1482
01:20:18,594 --> 01:20:23,177
Something that even time
can't hold from you.

1483
01:20:23,260 --> 01:20:27,469
I am not away from you,

1484
01:20:27,552 --> 01:20:32,135
I'm right there where you are too.

1485
01:20:32,844 --> 01:20:37,885
Now I am free of them too,

1486
01:20:38,302 --> 01:20:41,469
Whether or not I am there with you.

1487
01:20:41,552 --> 01:20:44,344
If not as a human, then as a Betaal...

1488
01:20:45,052 --> 01:20:47,635
I just wanted to stay with you, Alok.

1489
01:20:49,052 --> 01:20:51,427
Even if it was just
for a little while longer.

1490
01:20:52,677 --> 01:20:54,094
Why just a little longer?

1491
01:20:55,052 --> 01:20:58,510
Now I want to be
with you forever and ever and ever.

1492
01:21:01,344 --> 01:21:05,844
By the way, even dying a hundred
times for this kiss is totally worth it.

1493
01:21:06,427 --> 01:21:11,135
Whether or not I am there with you.

1494
01:21:11,219 --> 01:21:13,510
With you...

1495
01:21:14,052 --> 01:21:17,844
Like a bird,
I wish to fly through the boundless sky,

1496
01:21:17,969 --> 01:21:21,844
Today I'm free in the garden
where the world lies.

1497
01:21:21,927 --> 01:21:23,969
Like a bird, I wish to fly...

1498
01:21:24,052 --> 01:21:25,177
[evil laughter]

1499
01:21:25,469 --> 01:21:26,427
We've got good news!

1500
01:21:26,510 --> 01:21:27,552
[metal clanking]

1501
01:21:27,635 --> 01:21:31,385
How about treating me to the blood
of a diabetic as something sweet?

1502
01:21:31,760 --> 01:21:33,719
It's been ages since such fires were lit.

1503
01:21:34,427 --> 01:21:38,094
Tadaka bit that human
and turned him into a Betaal!

1504
01:21:39,427 --> 01:21:40,260
But Yakshasan...

1505
01:21:40,344 --> 01:21:41,719
No ifs or buts!

1506
01:21:42,677 --> 01:21:44,885
Your Thamma will be free...

1507
01:21:44,969 --> 01:21:47,969
And Tadaka will be locked away here.

1508
01:21:48,635 --> 01:21:50,719
[exhales heavily]

1509
01:21:51,594 --> 01:21:53,677
What's eating you, Rakhtash?

1510
01:21:54,927 --> 01:21:57,094
The king of kings is back.

1511
01:21:57,219 --> 01:21:58,802
Aren't you going to give me
a grand welcome?

1512
01:21:59,469 --> 01:22:00,969
Hurry up and make arrangements.

1513
01:22:01,052 --> 01:22:03,010
I'll get warmed up...

1514
01:22:04,010 --> 01:22:07,094
After all, soon I'll rule...
the world!

1515
01:22:07,177 --> 01:22:09,135
[evil laughter]

1516
01:22:09,219 --> 01:22:12,844
Like a bird,
I wish to fly through the boundless sky,

1517
01:22:12,927 --> 01:22:16,302
Today I'm free in the garden
where the world lies.

1518
01:22:18,302 --> 01:22:20,260
I've broken the cardinal rule,

1519
01:22:20,344 --> 01:22:23,302
and that could set Yakshasan free.

1520
01:22:23,760 --> 01:22:25,427
Who knows what he'll do then?

1521
01:22:25,510 --> 01:22:27,344
He'll drink human blood, obviously.

1522
01:22:27,844 --> 01:22:30,844
Tell me something, you Betaals...

1523
01:22:31,677 --> 01:22:32,260
Sorry...

1524
01:22:32,344 --> 01:22:35,885
"We" Betaals... why do we drink blood?

1525
01:22:36,802 --> 01:22:38,802
Did our ancestors not fancy
any other drink?

1526
01:22:39,094 --> 01:22:42,135
We need to kill humans
to recharge ourselves.

1527
01:22:42,219 --> 01:22:43,010
Ever thought about that?

1528
01:22:43,385 --> 01:22:44,094
No, never.

1529
01:22:45,302 --> 01:22:46,719
We weren't created to kill,

1530
01:22:47,677 --> 01:22:49,344
we were created to protect.

1531
01:22:49,844 --> 01:22:50,844
To protect?

1532
01:22:51,385 --> 01:22:54,469
The great demon Rakhtbeej
had a boon from Lord Shiva.

1533
01:22:55,135 --> 01:23:00,594
Every drop of his blood
would spawn another Rakhtbeej.

1534
01:23:01,135 --> 01:23:03,385
[music builds up]

1535
01:23:04,427 --> 01:23:07,594
When all the Gods lost to him,

1536
01:23:08,510 --> 01:23:10,344
they turned to the Goddess for help.

1537
01:23:11,677 --> 01:23:14,635
She fought fiercely with Rakhtbeej,

1538
01:23:15,094 --> 01:23:19,094
but every strike that drew his blood

1539
01:23:19,552 --> 01:23:22,885
created more Rakhtbeej.

1540
01:23:24,260 --> 01:23:27,302
So, to kill them and drink their blood,

1541
01:23:27,385 --> 01:23:29,885
the Goddess created Betaal.

1542
01:23:31,219 --> 01:23:32,302
[fire crackling]

1543
01:23:32,552 --> 01:23:33,844
Betaals:

1544
01:23:34,094 --> 01:23:36,052
born of darkness,

1545
01:23:36,719 --> 01:23:37,969
they drink blood,

1546
01:23:38,052 --> 01:23:39,427
they never die.

1547
01:23:39,802 --> 01:23:42,469
We were created to protect the earth.

1548
01:23:42,802 --> 01:23:46,552
All our rules exist for that.

1549
01:23:47,052 --> 01:23:49,427
Now you must follow them too,

1550
01:23:49,510 --> 01:23:50,969
to protect the earth.

1551
01:23:52,469 --> 01:23:55,469
How the hell am I supposed
to protect anyone when I'm scared stiff?

1552
01:23:55,844 --> 01:23:57,219
How can I protect the entire damn earth?

1553
01:23:57,302 --> 01:23:58,344
What if something happens to me?

1554
01:23:58,427 --> 01:23:59,094
How can I--

1555
01:23:59,177 --> 01:24:01,635
[Winces in pain]

1556
01:24:09,219 --> 01:24:11,052
Hey, drop the act...

1557
01:24:11,469 --> 01:24:12,427
you're absolutely fine.

1558
01:24:13,135 --> 01:24:14,344
[unzips the jacket]

1559
01:24:15,177 --> 01:24:16,260
You'll be indestructible.

1560
01:24:16,677 --> 01:24:17,844
You won't get hurt.

1561
01:24:18,094 --> 01:24:19,177
You won't feel any pain.

1562
01:24:19,469 --> 01:24:20,094
Got it?

1563
01:24:22,802 --> 01:24:24,177
This is crazy!

1564
01:24:25,969 --> 01:24:27,344
I'm slowly getting it.

1565
01:24:28,302 --> 01:24:30,052
You'll go through a lot of changes.

1566
01:24:30,719 --> 01:24:33,344
Now you've got to learn
to control yourself.

1567
01:24:34,469 --> 01:24:35,427
Control.

1568
01:24:37,427 --> 01:24:38,385
Control.

1569
01:24:38,469 --> 01:24:39,635
[cupboard door opens]

1570
01:24:41,552 --> 01:24:43,635
At first, the sun will bother you,

1571
01:24:44,010 --> 01:24:46,385
stepping out won't be easy.

1572
01:24:46,594 --> 01:24:48,802
But slowly, you'll get used to it.

1573
01:24:48,927 --> 01:24:49,927
Hey!

1574
01:24:50,219 --> 01:24:51,594
Your car's parked all crooked...
straighten it.

1575
01:24:54,260 --> 01:24:56,469
Your strength will grow immensely,

1576
01:24:56,677 --> 01:24:59,135
you won't even realize
how powerful you've become.

1577
01:24:59,677 --> 01:25:01,510
[peppy music]

1578
01:25:01,719 --> 01:25:02,719
[Beeping]

1579
01:25:02,802 --> 01:25:04,594
(Upbeat Music)

1580
01:25:06,094 --> 01:25:08,677
And your speed...
your speed will surpass even a cheetah's.

1581
01:25:18,135 --> 01:25:19,427
See you inside, sir.

1582
01:25:21,385 --> 01:25:23,427
(Upbeat Music)

1583
01:25:30,510 --> 01:25:33,885
The thirst for blood will grow
every time you see humans.

1584
01:25:34,469 --> 01:25:36,344
But you've got to control it.

1585
01:25:37,385 --> 01:25:38,969
(Upbeat Music)

1586
01:25:52,885 --> 01:25:53,427
Mummy...

1587
01:25:55,760 --> 01:25:57,594
[Hissing]

1588
01:26:02,469 --> 01:26:03,260
Alok...

1589
01:26:03,927 --> 01:26:05,177
Alok! Alok!

1590
01:26:06,094 --> 01:26:06,760
Open your mouth!

1591
01:26:06,969 --> 01:26:07,802
Show me your teeth!

1592
01:26:09,010 --> 01:26:11,677
Goyal, flash those punching-machine-like
teeth right now!

1593
01:26:11,760 --> 01:26:12,635
Are you a dentist?

1594
01:26:12,927 --> 01:26:14,052
The other day you wanted to see
the mole on my hip,

1595
01:26:14,135 --> 01:26:14,635
today you want to see my teeth.

1596
01:26:14,719 --> 01:26:15,594
I'm not showing them. What will you do?

1597
01:26:15,677 --> 01:26:16,927
- I'm out of here.
- Show them!

1598
01:26:20,635 --> 01:26:22,760
Where did they vanish to?

1599
01:26:23,385 --> 01:26:26,094
[growling]

1600
01:26:27,302 --> 01:26:28,969
This is what he does, Inspector!

1601
01:26:29,760 --> 01:26:31,427
My son is a demon.

1602
01:26:32,469 --> 01:26:36,135
That girl turned him into a demon.

1603
01:26:36,719 --> 01:26:39,844
She has got him under her spell.

1604
01:26:40,177 --> 01:26:42,802
She is a witch.

1605
01:26:43,010 --> 01:26:43,510
[Chuckling]

1606
01:26:43,594 --> 01:26:44,510
Come on, Mr. Goyal,

1607
01:26:44,760 --> 01:26:47,344
every in-law claims
their daughter-in-law is a witch.

1608
01:26:47,427 --> 01:26:48,969
She's not even my daughter-in-law.

1609
01:26:49,052 --> 01:26:49,927
Fine, your future daughter-in-law then.

1610
01:26:50,010 --> 01:26:52,344
How's she going to be
that if I don't let her?

1611
01:26:52,635 --> 01:26:55,635
Mr. Goyal, you call your son a demon,

1612
01:26:56,219 --> 01:26:57,677
and your daughter-in-law a witch.

1613
01:26:58,219 --> 01:26:59,052
What about your wife?

1614
01:26:59,302 --> 01:27:00,427
What do you think she is?

1615
01:27:01,094 --> 01:27:02,302
A vengeful spirit?

1616
01:27:02,385 --> 01:27:03,677
[laughing]

1617
01:27:05,844 --> 01:27:08,427
Now's not the time to laugh.

1618
01:27:08,802 --> 01:27:10,135
Save my son, please.

1619
01:27:10,594 --> 01:27:11,927
That girl's dangerous.

1620
01:27:12,427 --> 01:27:13,677
She can do anything.

1621
01:27:13,844 --> 01:27:16,677
Obviously, she is a woman.

1622
01:27:16,760 --> 01:27:18,010
Women can do anything.

1623
01:27:18,094 --> 01:27:19,052
But you're the police.

1624
01:27:19,135 --> 01:27:20,219
Aren't you going to do something?

1625
01:27:20,469 --> 01:27:21,469
Of course I am.

1626
01:27:21,969 --> 01:27:22,969
Tell me,

1627
01:27:23,552 --> 01:27:25,385
did you tell anyone else about this?

1628
01:27:25,469 --> 01:27:26,177
No. Not a word.

1629
01:27:26,260 --> 01:27:27,344
Good.

1630
01:27:27,594 --> 01:27:30,094
I'll make sure she's sent away.

1631
01:27:30,344 --> 01:27:32,052
Go home. P.K.

1632
01:27:32,135 --> 01:27:32,552
P.K.?

1633
01:27:32,635 --> 01:27:34,177
P.K. Yadav, Inspector.

1634
01:27:34,260 --> 01:27:34,969
Yes.

1635
01:27:35,177 --> 01:27:37,385
It's my job to send her away now.

1636
01:27:38,219 --> 01:27:39,594
Fine. It's your responsibility now.

1637
01:27:40,510 --> 01:27:41,427
Okay.

1638
01:27:42,177 --> 01:27:43,760
[Footsteps]

1639
01:27:49,969 --> 01:27:52,885
We have to end the new Betaal
to get Tadaka back.

1640
01:27:52,969 --> 01:27:53,635
No way.

1641
01:27:54,260 --> 01:27:55,177
We can't do that.

1642
01:27:56,260 --> 01:27:58,677
That's against the rules.

1643
01:27:59,344 --> 01:28:03,260
Then maybe it's time to change the rules.

1644
01:28:04,760 --> 01:28:06,760
Only a Thamma can change rules.

1645
01:28:07,385 --> 01:28:08,927
And we've got a Thamma.

1646
01:28:09,260 --> 01:28:10,344
Not our Thamma.

1647
01:28:11,802 --> 01:28:16,844
A Thamma with a heartbeat...

1648
01:28:18,177 --> 01:28:19,969
Only he can lead us forward.

1649
01:28:21,052 --> 01:28:22,010
That's nonsense.

1650
01:28:22,760 --> 01:28:27,052
Humans turn into Betaals
when their heart stops.

1651
01:28:28,302 --> 01:28:29,635
So how can Betaals' hero,

1652
01:28:30,260 --> 01:28:31,094
messiah,

1653
01:28:31,469 --> 01:28:32,344
the new Thamma,

1654
01:28:33,052 --> 01:28:34,427
have a heartbeat?

1655
01:28:35,427 --> 01:28:36,885
That's just folklore.

1656
01:28:37,427 --> 01:28:38,927
No one like that's ever coming.

1657
01:28:39,677 --> 01:28:41,594
Our Thamma's been the same
for centuries...

1658
01:28:42,594 --> 01:28:43,885
The Great Yakshasan.

1659
01:28:50,177 --> 01:28:52,969
Go find Tadaka and that Betaal
and bring them here.

1660
01:28:55,385 --> 01:28:58,052
[exhales heavily]

1661
01:29:04,052 --> 01:29:04,969
It's tough, huh?

1662
01:29:05,385 --> 01:29:06,260
I know.

1663
01:29:06,844 --> 01:29:07,719
Really tough.

1664
01:29:07,969 --> 01:29:08,802
Now jump.

1665
01:29:09,052 --> 01:29:09,469
Okay.

1666
01:29:09,552 --> 01:29:10,344
What?!

1667
01:29:10,760 --> 01:29:11,552
Jump.

1668
01:29:11,635 --> 01:29:12,719
- From here?
- Yes.

1669
01:29:15,052 --> 01:29:15,969
Are you serious?

1670
01:29:19,427 --> 01:29:21,094
[gentle music]

1671
01:29:36,344 --> 01:29:38,594
(Upbeat Music)

1672
01:29:43,344 --> 01:29:44,427
What was that?!

1673
01:29:44,719 --> 01:29:46,552
See? You were scared for nothing.

1674
01:29:46,802 --> 01:29:48,219
Me? Scared?
Nah, I don't scare that easily.

1675
01:29:48,302 --> 01:29:50,094
You offered your hand so sweetly that...

1676
01:29:50,177 --> 01:29:51,052
[growling]

1677
01:29:51,385 --> 01:29:52,052
Huh?

1678
01:29:53,385 --> 01:29:54,135
What's this?

1679
01:29:54,219 --> 01:29:55,510
You can't lie anymore.

1680
01:29:57,302 --> 01:29:59,760
Fangs pop out whenever we lie.

1681
01:30:00,010 --> 01:30:00,760
By themselves?

1682
01:30:00,844 --> 01:30:01,719
Uh-huh.

1683
01:30:02,219 --> 01:30:03,427
I can't even bloody lie anymore!

1684
01:30:04,344 --> 01:30:05,802
Control. Control.

1685
01:30:06,302 --> 01:30:07,385
Come on, let's go home.

1686
01:30:07,469 --> 01:30:08,510
Yes, let's go home.

1687
01:30:08,594 --> 01:30:09,552
Not like that.

1688
01:30:09,969 --> 01:30:10,969
How about we hop, skip,
and jump home?

1689
01:30:11,469 --> 01:30:12,302
Hop, skip, and jump?

1690
01:30:12,719 --> 01:30:14,594
(Upbeat Music)

1691
01:30:23,885 --> 01:30:24,719
[Sighs]

1692
01:30:28,927 --> 01:30:29,802
I'm good now.

1693
01:30:30,594 --> 01:30:32,219
Could do better.

1694
01:30:32,427 --> 01:30:34,469
There's a lot that's going
to get better now.

1695
01:30:34,552 --> 01:30:35,552
[Chuckling]

1696
01:30:38,052 --> 01:30:39,469
Dad! What are you doing in my room?

1697
01:30:39,552 --> 01:30:40,594
That's so creepy.

1698
01:30:41,219 --> 01:30:43,010
Who's being creepy here, me or you?

1699
01:30:43,469 --> 01:30:44,552
Where did you even come from?

1700
01:30:44,719 --> 01:30:45,552
Outside.

1701
01:30:45,802 --> 01:30:48,177
Everyone comes in from outside, son...

1702
01:30:48,260 --> 01:30:49,635
but through the door.

1703
01:30:49,719 --> 01:30:51,469
Not by jumping in through the balcony.

1704
01:30:51,594 --> 01:30:52,844
Are you stalking me?

1705
01:30:54,302 --> 01:30:55,385
Do you see anything written here?

1706
01:30:55,594 --> 01:30:56,802
Yes. No.

1707
01:30:56,885 --> 01:30:58,594
Then why are you assuming it?

1708
01:30:59,260 --> 01:31:00,594
Tell me, what are you hiding from me?

1709
01:31:01,135 --> 01:31:01,844
Nothing.

1710
01:31:01,927 --> 01:31:02,760
[Hissing]

1711
01:31:03,552 --> 01:31:04,344
What was that?

1712
01:31:04,427 --> 01:31:05,719
Nothing.
No, no, no...

1713
01:31:06,260 --> 01:31:06,969
Let me see.

1714
01:31:07,052 --> 01:31:08,510
- No. Just drop it.
- Let me see them.

1715
01:31:08,594 --> 01:31:09,010
Just let it go.

1716
01:31:09,094 --> 01:31:10,260
What's wrong with your nails?

1717
01:31:10,385 --> 01:31:10,969
- Just let it go.
- Let me see them!

1718
01:31:11,052 --> 01:31:11,969
[growling]

1719
01:31:12,052 --> 01:31:13,052
[Screaming]

1720
01:31:13,802 --> 01:31:16,510
The... the punching-machine-like teeth!

1721
01:31:16,594 --> 01:31:18,135
I was suspicious back at the hospital.

1722
01:31:18,219 --> 01:31:19,344
So I was right.

1723
01:31:20,219 --> 01:31:21,219
What's going on here?

1724
01:31:21,719 --> 01:31:23,052
Your son is dead.

1725
01:31:23,385 --> 01:31:24,260
But he's right here.

1726
01:31:24,344 --> 01:31:27,677
That day, he actually died
in a highway accident.

1727
01:31:29,927 --> 01:31:30,927
He died?

1728
01:31:31,635 --> 01:31:33,260
Then what is this?

1729
01:31:33,469 --> 01:31:34,719
His wandering soul?

1730
01:31:34,802 --> 01:31:35,677
The one that likes to wear a coat?

1731
01:31:35,927 --> 01:31:36,969
He's not a spirit.

1732
01:31:37,177 --> 01:31:37,844
Then?

1733
01:31:38,385 --> 01:31:40,385
I bit him and turned him like me.

1734
01:31:40,677 --> 01:31:41,469
Huh?

1735
01:31:41,885 --> 01:31:42,844
What do you mean "like you"?

1736
01:31:43,844 --> 01:31:45,010
So you're dead too?

1737
01:31:45,344 --> 01:31:45,969
[Hissing]

1738
01:31:46,052 --> 01:31:47,052
[Screaming]

1739
01:31:49,844 --> 01:31:53,760
What game are you playing with me?

1740
01:32:10,635 --> 01:32:12,427
My heart doesn't beat, Dad.

1741
01:32:15,969 --> 01:32:17,010
No heartbeat.

1742
01:32:18,677 --> 01:32:22,344
I know you won't believe it,
but it is what it is.

1743
01:32:27,885 --> 01:32:28,927
Aa... Alok...

1744
01:32:31,510 --> 01:32:32,385
Alok...

1745
01:32:35,302 --> 01:32:36,135
Alok...

1746
01:32:38,719 --> 01:32:39,969
My son...

1747
01:32:43,635 --> 01:32:44,927
[Sobs]

1748
01:32:46,219 --> 01:32:47,135
You...

1749
01:32:47,552 --> 01:32:49,427
You... you're dead?

1750
01:32:52,510 --> 01:32:53,552
[Sobs]

1751
01:32:53,635 --> 01:32:55,302
If I tell Sudha, she'd...

1752
01:32:59,969 --> 01:33:03,469
We thought you'd support us in old age.

1753
01:33:04,052 --> 01:33:05,177
I will, Dad.

1754
01:33:06,344 --> 01:33:07,677
Now, I'll be your evergreen support.

1755
01:33:08,844 --> 01:33:10,177
You'll grow old,

1756
01:33:10,635 --> 01:33:12,385
but your support will always stay young.

1757
01:33:13,177 --> 01:33:15,719
No, you're not Alok.

1758
01:33:16,719 --> 01:33:18,969
You're my son's spirit. You're not Alok.

1759
01:33:19,052 --> 01:33:20,552
I'm not a spirit, Dad...

1760
01:33:21,094 --> 01:33:22,635
but close.

1761
01:33:24,844 --> 01:33:25,927
I'm a Betaal.

1762
01:33:26,677 --> 01:33:27,677
Betaal?

1763
01:33:28,802 --> 01:33:30,635
That's what our species are called.

1764
01:33:31,094 --> 01:33:32,469
[Footsteps]

1765
01:33:33,385 --> 01:33:34,885
He has turned into a Betaal.

1766
01:33:37,177 --> 01:33:38,302
I knew it!

1767
01:33:38,469 --> 01:33:42,094
I knew you "witch"
would spell doom for my son!

1768
01:33:42,635 --> 01:33:45,385
If I hadn't done this,
he'd have died in the hospital.

1769
01:33:46,510 --> 01:33:48,427
I couldn't let him die.

1770
01:33:50,641 --> 01:33:52,219
I love Alok.

1771
01:33:53,427 --> 01:33:55,469
Couldn't you love someone else?

1772
01:33:56,385 --> 01:33:58,552
You should've chosen someone
from your own community.

1773
01:33:59,135 --> 01:34:01,427
Some tall, dark, red-eyed guy with fangs.

1774
01:34:03,969 --> 01:34:05,427
Don't worry, son.

1775
01:34:06,010 --> 01:34:07,885
I'll get the best doctor.

1776
01:34:08,427 --> 01:34:10,010
I'll get the best heart doctor,

1777
01:34:10,094 --> 01:34:13,760
transplant your heart,
bring your heartbeat back.

1778
01:34:14,094 --> 01:34:15,427
Doctors can't help, Dad.

1779
01:34:15,552 --> 01:34:20,177
If not a doctor, then a tantric
or miracle performing sage could help.

1780
01:34:20,260 --> 01:34:21,552
No one can do anything, Dad.

1781
01:34:22,719 --> 01:34:23,844
Not even God.

1782
01:34:27,052 --> 01:34:30,219
How about the hand of God?

1783
01:34:30,885 --> 01:34:31,677
Hmm?

1784
01:34:32,427 --> 01:34:33,427
Don't worry, son.

1785
01:34:34,010 --> 01:34:36,677
The hand of God is with youuuu.

1786
01:34:37,010 --> 01:34:39,052
Why don't you get it?

1787
01:34:40,260 --> 01:34:41,719
How do I explain?

1788
01:34:42,594 --> 01:34:44,969
I'll tell you a story. Listen carefully.

1789
01:34:45,344 --> 01:34:49,510
It's a full moon night,
moonlight falls on the earth...

1790
01:34:49,594 --> 01:34:51,302
And the moment it hits, my brother goes...

1791
01:34:55,427 --> 01:34:56,385
Grrrr!

1792
01:34:56,719 --> 01:34:57,594
Grrrr?!

1793
01:34:57,802 --> 01:34:59,052
Grrrr!

1794
01:34:59,927 --> 01:35:02,010
Oh my God,
your brother's a Bhediya (wolf)!

1795
01:35:02,094 --> 01:35:03,677
Exactly!

1796
01:35:03,760 --> 01:35:05,177
Yes! Yes! Yes!

1797
01:35:05,260 --> 01:35:06,010
Yes.

1798
01:35:06,094 --> 01:35:08,844
He's a perverted human,
with a wolf inside.

1799
01:35:09,177 --> 01:35:11,885
Amazing! We desperately need a Bhediya .

1800
01:35:11,969 --> 01:35:12,760
Okay.

1801
01:35:13,969 --> 01:35:15,094
Tell me,

1802
01:35:16,594 --> 01:35:18,385
how exactly did your brother
turn into a Bhediya ?

1803
01:35:18,760 --> 01:35:20,177
Long story.

1804
01:35:20,260 --> 01:35:22,469
You could easily make a movie
with a post-credit scene out of it.

1805
01:35:22,552 --> 01:35:23,635
I'll tell you some other time.

1806
01:35:23,719 --> 01:35:25,219
Right now, I am here because
he's dealing with a big problem.

1807
01:35:25,302 --> 01:35:26,135
So just hear me out.

1808
01:35:26,219 --> 01:35:28,469
Why are you here instead of him?

1809
01:35:29,344 --> 01:35:34,427
He's been thrashed so badly,
he can't face anyone anymore.

1810
01:35:34,844 --> 01:35:37,177
Impossible! Bhediya is so powerful!

1811
01:35:37,427 --> 01:35:38,719
Who thrashed him?

1812
01:35:39,510 --> 01:35:43,510
A monster... with a chopped off thingy.

1813
01:35:43,635 --> 01:35:44,802
With a chopped off what?

1814
01:35:45,094 --> 01:35:46,510
A chopped-off body part.

1815
01:35:47,219 --> 01:35:48,177
During the fight,

1816
01:35:48,719 --> 01:35:51,927
that monster did things I can't even say.

1817
01:35:53,552 --> 01:35:54,677
He did that?

1818
01:35:54,760 --> 01:35:56,260
No, he didn't do THAT!

1819
01:35:56,719 --> 01:35:57,344
Come on, man!

1820
01:35:57,427 --> 01:35:59,302
My brother fought the monster.

1821
01:35:59,510 --> 01:36:01,219
So the monster thrashed him so badly...

1822
01:36:01,594 --> 01:36:02,635
How did he thrash him?

1823
01:36:02,802 --> 01:36:03,760
Like this.

1824
01:36:07,927 --> 01:36:10,135
Now that poor guy
can't fully turn into a Bhediya .

1825
01:36:10,219 --> 01:36:12,052
All he can do is... Dame Un Grrr!

1826
01:36:13,010 --> 01:36:14,427
You're quite skilled.

1827
01:36:14,844 --> 01:36:17,094
You helped capture that wretched Munjya .

1828
01:36:17,885 --> 01:36:20,094
You've got a solution for this too, right?

1829
01:36:20,177 --> 01:36:22,260
Any powder, pill, elixir of life?
Anything?

1830
01:36:22,552 --> 01:36:24,427
Think with your mind, not your hand.

1831
01:36:24,885 --> 01:36:26,052
(Gibberish)

1832
01:36:26,552 --> 01:36:27,344
Stop it.

1833
01:36:31,552 --> 01:36:32,469
Hey, Padre!

1834
01:36:32,552 --> 01:36:33,552
[Table bell ringing]

1835
01:36:33,635 --> 01:36:34,594
Padre, my brother?

1836
01:36:35,802 --> 01:36:37,302
[dramatic music]

1837
01:36:41,427 --> 01:36:42,594
Hey!

1838
01:36:45,927 --> 01:36:47,094
That's my brother! That's my brother!

1839
01:36:47,260 --> 01:36:49,385
Yes, Bhediya :

1840
01:36:49,969 --> 01:36:51,135
The protector of the jungle!

1841
01:36:51,219 --> 01:36:51,844
Right.

1842
01:36:51,927 --> 01:36:56,052
To boost his power, he needs
to drink the blood

1843
01:36:57,052 --> 01:36:58,427
of a bloodsucker.

1844
01:36:58,677 --> 01:36:59,885
A bloodsucker?

1845
01:37:00,469 --> 01:37:02,052
A leech! You mean a leech!

1846
01:37:02,135 --> 01:37:04,177
[laughing]

1847
01:37:07,260 --> 01:37:08,510
No,

1848
01:37:09,260 --> 01:37:11,010
I mean a special species.

1849
01:37:11,594 --> 01:37:15,260
They look like humans
and drink human blood.

1850
01:37:17,469 --> 01:37:18,719
Betaal!

1851
01:37:20,802 --> 01:37:25,885
He sinks his fangs right into the vein
and drinks the blood.

1852
01:37:25,969 --> 01:37:26,635
Yes.

1853
01:37:26,719 --> 01:37:27,885
Like Dracula?

1854
01:37:28,260 --> 01:37:29,177
Something like that.

1855
01:37:30,094 --> 01:37:32,260
But that species is extinct.

1856
01:37:32,385 --> 01:37:34,469
Extinct? No, don't say that.

1857
01:37:36,469 --> 01:37:37,469
[Clears throat]

1858
01:37:38,219 --> 01:37:40,094
Sorry, It looks difficult.

1859
01:37:40,427 --> 01:37:42,135
You keep shouting,
"Hand of God! Hand of God!"

1860
01:37:42,219 --> 01:37:43,427
You've got to do something.

1861
01:37:43,885 --> 01:37:44,802
Don't you know that

1862
01:37:44,885 --> 01:37:47,385
the glaciers are melting
and extinct species are coming back?

1863
01:37:47,469 --> 01:37:50,385
Huge tusked elephants, flying crocodiles,
good actors.

1864
01:37:51,177 --> 01:37:53,094
Padre, please, just two minutes.

1865
01:37:53,260 --> 01:37:54,094
Just two minutes.

1866
01:37:54,760 --> 01:37:56,052
- What happened?
- There's an emergency.

1867
01:37:56,135 --> 01:37:56,969
What's the emergency?

1868
01:37:57,052 --> 01:37:58,719
Am I invisible or what?

1869
01:37:58,885 --> 01:38:00,177
I'm still sitting here talking to him,
and you just barged in!

1870
01:38:00,260 --> 01:38:01,635
A desperate father is begging you.

1871
01:38:01,719 --> 01:38:02,635
Only two minutes.

1872
01:38:02,802 --> 01:38:03,510
Please.

1873
01:38:03,594 --> 01:38:06,510
No, Uncle, don't. You can take three.

1874
01:38:07,552 --> 01:38:08,885
Thank you, son, thank you.

1875
01:38:10,385 --> 01:38:12,219
Bittu! What are you doing in Delhi, bro?

1876
01:38:13,344 --> 01:38:14,177
Who's Bittu?

1877
01:38:21,219 --> 01:38:23,802
Now, what's the emergency?

1878
01:38:23,885 --> 01:38:25,010
The emergency...

1879
01:38:25,302 --> 01:38:29,844
Sir, there's a boy who a witchy girl...

1880
01:38:29,927 --> 01:38:32,094
- Dad...
- Give me a minute, let me explain.

1881
01:38:33,469 --> 01:38:40,427
A boy was bitten here by a witchy girl.

1882
01:38:41,677 --> 01:38:44,844
Now he's become like her.

1883
01:38:45,385 --> 01:38:46,344
Sex change?

1884
01:38:46,510 --> 01:38:48,385
No, no, no sex change.

1885
01:38:48,469 --> 01:38:52,094
He's turned into a demon, just like her.

1886
01:38:52,719 --> 01:38:54,177
His heart doesn't beat.

1887
01:38:54,552 --> 01:38:56,094
He gets wild at the sight of blood.

1888
01:38:56,635 --> 01:38:59,094
He's dead, yet alive.

1889
01:39:00,510 --> 01:39:02,260
You are talking about him, right?

1890
01:39:02,510 --> 01:39:04,469
No sir, he's talking about someone else.

1891
01:39:04,552 --> 01:39:05,719
[growling]

1892
01:39:06,052 --> 01:39:08,010
Hey! Hey Betaal!

1893
01:39:10,385 --> 01:39:11,385
Miracle!

1894
01:39:11,594 --> 01:39:12,427
Miracle!

1895
01:39:12,552 --> 01:39:13,427
Miracle!

1896
01:39:13,510 --> 01:39:15,385
What a coincidence!

1897
01:39:15,469 --> 01:39:16,719
What a coincidence!

1898
01:39:16,844 --> 01:39:17,760
You know about them?

1899
01:39:17,885 --> 01:39:18,344
Yes.

1900
01:39:18,427 --> 01:39:21,427
I knew it! I knew you'd know!

1901
01:39:21,510 --> 01:39:23,427
So tell me Padre,

1902
01:39:23,510 --> 01:39:26,594
is there any way to cure a Betaal
and make him human again?

1903
01:39:27,385 --> 01:39:29,677
You can make an omelette
from an egg, right?

1904
01:39:29,885 --> 01:39:30,927
Right.

1905
01:39:31,260 --> 01:39:33,552
But can an omelette ever turn back
into an egg?

1906
01:39:34,219 --> 01:39:36,010
I wouldn't know... I'm vegetarian.

1907
01:39:36,510 --> 01:39:37,594
Oh.

1908
01:39:38,260 --> 01:39:38,927
Then...

1909
01:39:39,010 --> 01:39:41,260
You can make ketchup from tomatoes, right?

1910
01:39:41,510 --> 01:39:42,385
Right.

1911
01:39:42,469 --> 01:39:44,552
But can ketchup ever turn back
into tomatoes?

1912
01:39:44,760 --> 01:39:46,469
- No. No way.
- No.

1913
01:39:46,552 --> 01:39:49,552
Similarly, human to Betaal, possible.

1914
01:39:50,219 --> 01:39:51,760
But Betaal to human...

1915
01:39:52,885 --> 01:39:53,719
impossible.

1916
01:39:55,469 --> 01:39:55,802
[Sobs]

1917
01:39:55,885 --> 01:39:57,010
Don't say that.

1918
01:39:57,760 --> 01:39:59,302
Don't say it, please.

1919
01:39:59,760 --> 01:40:01,469
You don't say that.

1920
01:40:01,969 --> 01:40:03,094
Be happy.

1921
01:40:04,219 --> 01:40:05,552
Congratulations.

1922
01:40:05,635 --> 01:40:06,552
For what?

1923
01:40:07,177 --> 01:40:10,927
Your family's light can't be extinguished
even with a fire extinguisher.

1924
01:40:11,385 --> 01:40:12,677
He's immortal.

1925
01:40:12,844 --> 01:40:15,969
You're our last hope.

1926
01:40:16,302 --> 01:40:17,510
Please save him.

1927
01:40:17,594 --> 01:40:18,552
Please.

1928
01:40:18,885 --> 01:40:20,052
Please save him.

1929
01:40:20,469 --> 01:40:22,177
I can understand your feelings.

1930
01:40:23,469 --> 01:40:25,552
But I am telling you
with all my experience...

1931
01:40:26,344 --> 01:40:27,677
Nothing can be done.

1932
01:40:29,302 --> 01:40:30,344
Accept it.

1933
01:40:31,552 --> 01:40:32,802
There is no cure?

1934
01:40:35,510 --> 01:40:36,469
No chance.

1935
01:40:40,760 --> 01:40:41,552
Alok?

1936
01:40:42,052 --> 01:40:42,885
Goyal?

1937
01:40:43,885 --> 01:40:44,552
Goyal?!

1938
01:40:44,635 --> 01:40:45,260
Greetings, Uncle.

1939
01:40:45,344 --> 01:40:46,969
Sir, don't forget
to transfer my fees of Rs. 10,000!

1940
01:40:47,552 --> 01:40:48,594
Alok, listen...

1941
01:40:48,844 --> 01:40:50,885
Why should I listen to you?
Why should I, huh?

1942
01:40:51,719 --> 01:40:56,219
The girl you call a witch
and demon gave me a new life.

1943
01:40:57,094 --> 01:40:59,260
And your son loves her.

1944
01:41:00,302 --> 01:41:01,510
And he always will.

1945
01:41:04,135 --> 01:41:05,635
[whistling]

1946
01:41:06,969 --> 01:41:08,094
That's no way to call anyone.

1947
01:41:08,219 --> 01:41:09,927
I have a name - Jana, JD, Janardhan.

1948
01:41:11,385 --> 01:41:12,260
What is it?

1949
01:41:14,719 --> 01:41:15,010
[tongue click]

1950
01:41:15,135 --> 01:41:15,719
What?

1951
01:41:15,802 --> 01:41:17,385
(Indistinct)

1952
01:41:18,760 --> 01:41:19,635
What are you saying?

1953
01:41:21,052 --> 01:41:22,844
(Indistinct)

1954
01:41:23,427 --> 01:41:25,219
[laughing]

1955
01:41:26,927 --> 01:41:28,427
Thank you, Padre. Thank you.

1956
01:41:31,427 --> 01:41:31,844
[whistling]

1957
01:41:31,927 --> 01:41:32,635
Gift!

1958
01:41:33,760 --> 01:41:35,469
Make your brother sniff it.

1959
01:41:36,677 --> 01:41:37,635
Elixir of life.

1960
01:41:38,094 --> 01:41:39,177
- Yes.
- Yes.

1961
01:41:39,260 --> 01:41:40,302
Okay.

1962
01:41:40,427 --> 01:41:43,135
Miracle! Miracle! Miracle! Miracle!

1963
01:41:45,677 --> 01:41:47,677
[Indistinct Chattering]

1964
01:41:56,302 --> 01:41:58,010
[dramatic music]

1965
01:42:10,469 --> 01:42:12,469
[panting]

1966
01:42:14,052 --> 01:42:15,844
Mom, give the phone to Tarika.

1967
01:42:15,927 --> 01:42:16,885
Okay, hang on.

1968
01:42:16,969 --> 01:42:17,802
Alok.

1969
01:42:19,594 --> 01:42:21,219
Tarika, listen up.

1970
01:42:21,677 --> 01:42:24,094
Those guys from your tribe who were
chasing us in the jungle the other day...

1971
01:42:24,510 --> 01:42:25,510
they're here.

1972
01:42:26,052 --> 01:42:26,969
They're following me.

1973
01:42:27,052 --> 01:42:29,427
Alok, get out of there now.

1974
01:42:29,510 --> 01:42:31,260
Get to high ground, I'm on my way.

1975
01:42:31,344 --> 01:42:32,677
Okay.

1976
01:42:50,677 --> 01:42:51,802
Hey, are you blind of what?

1977
01:42:51,885 --> 01:42:52,219
[Hissing]

1978
01:42:52,302 --> 01:42:53,094
Hey!

1979
01:42:53,469 --> 01:42:54,302
Hey!

1980
01:42:58,927 --> 01:43:00,802
[music builds up]

1981
01:43:17,219 --> 01:43:18,677
[Traffic Noise]

1982
01:43:29,469 --> 01:43:31,510
[bats screeching]

1983
01:43:51,510 --> 01:43:52,719
[loud thud]

1984
01:43:54,260 --> 01:43:56,427
[intense music]

1985
01:44:11,719 --> 01:44:13,260
Who the hell are you?

1986
01:44:13,719 --> 01:44:14,969
And why'd you fling that rag in my face?

1987
01:44:15,094 --> 01:44:16,052
Forget the rag...

1988
01:44:16,427 --> 01:44:18,302
I know all about you.

1989
01:44:18,635 --> 01:44:19,594
What...

1990
01:44:20,052 --> 01:44:21,010
what do you know?

1991
01:44:21,094 --> 01:44:23,094
I know you're a Betaal.

1992
01:44:24,135 --> 01:44:25,177
Doesn't matter who I am.

1993
01:44:25,844 --> 01:44:27,219
What do you want, bro?

1994
01:44:27,885 --> 01:44:29,260
Your blood.

1995
01:44:29,594 --> 01:44:31,677
Oh, you Wannabe Wolverine,

1996
01:44:31,927 --> 01:44:33,427
you're going to resort
to bloodshed now, huh?

1997
01:44:33,510 --> 01:44:36,469
Hey Dracula on a budget!

1998
01:44:37,135 --> 01:44:39,510
I will drink your blood today.

1999
01:44:40,427 --> 01:44:41,510
[growling]

2000
01:44:41,677 --> 01:44:42,677
What's with the overacting?

2001
01:44:42,760 --> 01:44:44,260
Who's overacting, huh?

2002
01:44:54,510 --> 01:44:55,427
[growling]

2003
01:44:56,927 --> 01:44:59,052
[Grunts]

2004
01:45:11,427 --> 01:45:14,385
[growling]

2005
01:45:41,927 --> 01:45:43,010
Cut the crap.

2006
01:45:43,552 --> 01:45:44,927
Let me have your blood, or else...

2007
01:45:45,135 --> 01:45:46,177
Why the hell do you even want blood?

2008
01:45:47,010 --> 01:45:48,552
I'm the one who drinks blood here.

2009
01:45:53,427 --> 01:45:54,219
[Grunts]

2010
