didn't sit well with you.

2186
01:56:46,927 --> 01:56:48,010
Where's Tarika?

2187
01:56:48,427 --> 01:56:49,469
She's gone.

2188
01:56:51,344 --> 01:56:52,260
Gone?

2189
01:56:53,302 --> 01:56:54,427
How can she just leave?

2190
01:56:56,177 --> 01:56:57,635
I sent her back...

2191
01:56:59,427 --> 01:57:00,302
with Veeran.

2192
01:57:05,219 --> 01:57:06,802
She didn't tell you everything.

2193
01:57:08,344 --> 01:57:09,302
About what?

2194
01:57:15,552 --> 01:57:16,427
[Hissing]

2195
01:57:16,844 --> 01:57:17,594
Come on, Tadaka.

2196
01:57:18,344 --> 01:57:19,719
It's time to head back.

2197
01:57:20,177 --> 01:57:21,052
No.

2198
01:57:22,677 --> 01:57:25,052
[growling]

2199
01:57:27,677 --> 01:57:29,219
You have to go back.

2200
01:57:29,844 --> 01:57:31,844
You broke the cardinal rule.

2201
01:57:33,885 --> 01:57:35,635
The day you bit Alok,

2202
01:57:36,177 --> 01:57:38,635
you knew this would happen.

2203
01:57:39,552 --> 01:57:41,302
Now Yakshasan will be free,

2204
01:57:41,510 --> 01:57:43,260
and you'll be locked up instead.

2205
01:57:43,719 --> 01:57:44,760
For a hundred years.

2206
01:57:45,177 --> 01:57:45,927
No.

2207
01:57:46,010 --> 01:57:47,927
I'm not leaving Alok.

2208
01:57:48,344 --> 01:57:52,802
You knew biting Alok meant
your imprisonment,

2209
01:57:53,427 --> 01:57:54,552
yet you broke the rule.

2210
01:57:59,427 --> 01:58:00,385
But Alok?

2211
01:58:01,052 --> 01:58:02,552
Bhediya is hunting him.

2212
01:58:03,510 --> 01:58:06,677
We'll keep Alok safe here.

2213
01:58:07,385 --> 01:58:08,969
But that means you have to go.

2214
01:58:11,427 --> 01:58:13,385
Do you want to save him or not?

2215
01:58:17,302 --> 01:58:19,594
I have no intention of dying together.

2216
01:58:21,052 --> 01:58:22,594
How about
we live together instead, hmm?!

2217
01:58:26,552 --> 01:58:28,719
Can I see him once before I leave?

2218
01:58:39,135 --> 01:58:41,385
[intense music]

2219
01:58:44,302 --> 01:58:49,802
Didn't think this is how we would part ways

2220
01:58:49,885 --> 01:58:55,094
I have so many things still left to say

2221
01:58:55,177 --> 01:59:00,635
Impossible that you
will ever escape my heart

2222
01:59:00,760 --> 01:59:05,969
Wish I could take us back to the start...

2223
01:59:06,052 --> 01:59:07,677
Tarika risked everything to save me?

2224
01:59:09,052 --> 01:59:10,260
Why didn't she tell me?

2225
01:59:11,385 --> 01:59:12,552
I have to go find her.

2226
01:59:12,927 --> 01:59:14,094
You're not going anywhere!

2227
01:59:14,177 --> 01:59:16,219
[growling]

2228
01:59:30,177 --> 01:59:32,177
There's a dangerous Bhediya out there.

2229
01:59:33,552 --> 01:59:35,969
You'll stay in this city,
under our watch.

2230
01:59:36,594 --> 01:59:37,469
And Tarika?

2231
01:59:37,552 --> 01:59:38,385
Forget her.

2232
01:59:39,010 --> 01:59:39,927
Just forget about her.

2233
01:59:41,302 --> 01:59:42,760
Go home and stay low.

2234
01:59:42,927 --> 01:59:45,094
Don't step out unless I say so.

2235
01:59:46,302 --> 01:59:47,219
Understood?

2236
01:59:48,635 --> 01:59:49,594
Did you hear me?

2237
02:00:00,552 --> 02:00:01,552
Where were you all night?

2238
02:00:02,635 --> 02:00:03,635
Tarika's not home either.

2239
02:00:04,594 --> 02:00:05,427
She's gone.

2240
02:00:05,760 --> 02:00:06,594
Where to?

2241
02:00:07,385 --> 02:00:08,552
Back where she came from.

2242
02:00:10,177 --> 02:00:12,844
She broke their cardinal rule for me.

2243
02:00:14,469 --> 02:00:16,302
Now she'll be punished for it...
for eternity.

2244
02:00:18,594 --> 02:00:19,802
And I'll be stuck here...

2245
02:00:21,469 --> 02:00:22,469
without Tarika.

2246
02:00:24,552 --> 02:00:27,594
Maybe that's my punishment.

2247
02:00:30,594 --> 02:00:31,594
Goyal...

2248
02:00:33,760 --> 02:00:36,969
I thought hard after meeting that Padre.

2249
02:00:37,802 --> 02:00:40,302
Now I finally get it.

2250
02:00:41,135 --> 02:00:43,260
Whoever you are...

2251
02:00:44,510 --> 02:00:46,052
Dead or alive...

2252
02:00:47,552 --> 02:00:48,635
you're still my son.

2253
02:00:50,094 --> 02:00:51,385
You might drink blood...

2254
02:00:51,885 --> 02:00:53,552
but you're still my flesh and blood.

2255
02:00:53,969 --> 02:00:54,927
Go ahead, drink it.

2256
02:00:56,635 --> 02:00:59,010
I'm already 60.

2257
02:01:00,594 --> 02:01:03,552
For approximately the next 40 years,

2258
02:01:04,010 --> 02:01:06,010
Tarika's my daughter-in-law.

2259
02:01:07,177 --> 02:01:07,927
Daughter-in-law?

2260
02:01:08,844 --> 02:01:09,844
Look,

2261
02:01:10,177 --> 02:01:13,427
no one else can stay
with you this long anyway.

2262
02:01:13,927 --> 02:01:15,677
At least, not a human.

2263
02:01:17,760 --> 02:01:20,760
Your heart doesn't beat,

2264
02:01:21,469 --> 02:01:23,719
but it still loves Tarika.

2265
02:01:25,094 --> 02:01:27,885
That love helps you stay human.

2266
02:01:28,510 --> 02:01:31,177
Go... bring her back.

2267
02:01:32,427 --> 02:01:33,927
I can't, Dad.

2268
02:01:34,677 --> 02:01:36,844
Their rules won't let me leave.

2269
02:01:37,005 --> 02:01:39,088
What rules? Which rules?

2270
02:01:39,635 --> 02:01:42,969
Tarika broke every rule to be
with you, right?

2271
02:01:43,219 --> 02:01:44,052
Didn't she?

2272
02:01:44,677 --> 02:01:47,302
Then you should break every rule too,
just to be with her.

2273
02:01:47,677 --> 02:01:48,344
Come on now.

2274
02:01:48,427 --> 02:01:49,302
Come on. Get up.

2275
02:01:51,302 --> 02:01:52,302
Go, Goyal.

2276
02:01:52,552 --> 02:01:54,844
Enjoy your life after death.

2277
02:01:56,052 --> 02:01:57,302
Live long.

2278
02:01:57,927 --> 02:02:00,094
[intense music]

2279
02:02:08,385 --> 02:02:10,719
[footsteps, dried leaves crunching]

2280
02:03:14,302 --> 02:03:17,135
[footsteps, dried leaves crunching]

2281
02:03:23,677 --> 02:03:26,094
[suspense music]

2282
02:03:35,969 --> 02:03:39,469
Thamma! Thamma! Thamma! Thamma!

2283
02:03:52,635 --> 02:03:58,885
[Mystical song]

2284
02:04:08,719 --> 02:04:10,302
[Mystical music]

2285
02:04:15,719 --> 02:04:17,510
[metal clanking]

2286
02:04:18,302 --> 02:04:23,177
I can't explain how good
I feel being free after 75 years!

2287
02:04:25,260 --> 02:04:26,802
That dark cave bored me to death.

2288
02:04:28,594 --> 02:04:30,177
While singing to kill time,

2289
02:04:30,635 --> 02:04:33,302
the throat-slasher got a sore throat.

2290
02:04:35,635 --> 02:04:37,135
Did you lot get a sore throat too?

2291
02:04:37,927 --> 02:04:39,219
Speak up!

2292
02:04:40,844 --> 02:04:41,844
Thamma!

2293
02:04:41,927 --> 02:04:42,885
Thamma!

2294
02:04:42,969 --> 02:04:44,135
Louder!

2295
02:04:44,219 --> 02:04:45,010
Thamma!

2296
02:04:45,094 --> 02:04:46,302
All together now!

2297
02:04:46,385 --> 02:04:47,385
Thamma! Thamma!

2298
02:04:47,469 --> 02:04:48,885
Thamma! Thamma!

2299
02:04:48,969 --> 02:04:49,802
Thamma!

2300
02:04:49,885 --> 02:04:51,635
Thamma! Thamma!

2301
02:04:51,719 --> 02:04:52,844
Thamma! Thamma!

2302
02:04:52,927 --> 02:04:55,010
I've been longing to hear this.

2303
02:04:56,135 --> 02:04:58,760
From today, your Thamma is free.

2304
02:04:58,844 --> 02:05:00,177
[evil laughter]

2305
02:05:01,885 --> 02:05:06,177
And from now on,
whatever I say becomes law.

2306
02:05:07,302 --> 02:05:08,802
We'll drink human blood,

2307
02:05:08,885 --> 02:05:10,177
spawn new Betaals,

2308
02:05:10,260 --> 02:05:11,219
build our army.

2309
02:05:12,469 --> 02:05:13,719
And she will be freed too.

2310
02:05:15,427 --> 02:05:16,219
Are you ready?

2311
02:05:19,760 --> 02:05:20,760
As you wish.

2312
02:05:22,510 --> 02:05:24,760
Meanwhile, will you do the honours
of chanting the mantras?

2313
02:05:26,510 --> 02:05:28,885
Can't you see I wanna break free?

2314
02:05:29,427 --> 02:05:30,427
Hurry up!

2315
02:05:30,510 --> 02:05:33,219
Thamma! Thamma! Thamma! Thamma!

2316
02:05:37,885 --> 02:05:40,219
Hundred years of toil and pain,

2317
02:05:41,385 --> 02:05:43,927
Hundred years bound in fire's chain,

2318
02:05:44,719 --> 02:05:46,385
Liberate the body's frame,

2319
02:05:47,635 --> 02:05:49,427
Liberate the soul the same.

2320
02:05:49,510 --> 02:05:50,885
[metal clanking]

2321
02:05:58,844 --> 02:06:00,260
[Sighs]

2322
02:06:01,469 --> 02:06:02,427
Tadaka...

2323
02:06:03,802 --> 02:06:04,885
Thank you.

2324
02:06:05,927 --> 02:06:09,594
The first time you ran away
with that boy, I knew

2325
02:06:10,219 --> 02:06:11,844
"This is the girl

2326
02:06:13,135 --> 02:06:14,260
who'll free me

2327
02:06:14,344 --> 02:06:17,802
and trap herself in love...

2328
02:06:18,552 --> 02:06:19,594
and shackles too."

2329
02:06:19,677 --> 02:06:21,510
[evil laughter]

2330
02:06:23,052 --> 02:06:24,302
You could still be free.

2331
02:06:24,885 --> 02:06:27,927
But I'm sorry, he's not agreeing.

2332
02:06:28,969 --> 02:06:30,969
So now, thanks again,

2333
02:06:31,760 --> 02:06:33,260
from the bottom of my heart.

2334
02:06:34,927 --> 02:06:35,885
Bye-bye...

2335
02:06:36,344 --> 02:06:37,510
for a hundred years.

2336
02:06:40,052 --> 02:06:41,677
Thamma! Thamma!

2337
02:06:41,760 --> 02:06:44,052
Thamma! Thamma!

2338
02:06:44,135 --> 02:06:44,885
Take her away.

2339
02:06:44,969 --> 02:06:45,969
Thamma! Thamma!

2340
02:06:46,052 --> 02:06:47,260
Excuse me, mister.

2341
02:06:50,010 --> 02:06:50,927
Alok?

2342
02:06:51,927 --> 02:06:52,885
Hi.

2343
02:06:53,135 --> 02:06:54,385
What are you doing here?

2344
02:06:54,927 --> 02:06:56,219
I'm here to taste a Barasingha
(Reindeer).

2345
02:06:56,302 --> 02:06:56,969
What?

2346
02:06:57,052 --> 02:06:58,177
It's your favourite, right?

2347
02:06:58,385 --> 02:06:59,135
Alok!

2348
02:06:59,219 --> 02:07:00,719
I'm here for you, obviously.

2349
02:07:01,302 --> 02:07:02,802
You're getting locked up for 100 years

2350
02:07:02,969 --> 02:07:04,260
and didn't even care inform me.

2351
02:07:04,344 --> 02:07:05,302
That's not fair.

2352
02:07:05,385 --> 02:07:07,344
Alok, forget all this and just run.

2353
02:07:07,760 --> 02:07:08,927
I have to take this punishment.

2354
02:07:09,010 --> 02:07:09,802
I broke the rule.

2355
02:07:09,885 --> 02:07:11,094
To hell with rules.

2356
02:07:11,552 --> 02:07:13,885
Yaku sir... I mean, Yakshasan sir.

2357
02:07:14,469 --> 02:07:16,260
Sir, I'm not here to fight,
I'm here to talk.

2358
02:07:16,635 --> 02:07:17,844
Let's negotiate, okay?

2359
02:07:18,177 --> 02:07:19,552
Hundred years is too much.

2360
02:07:20,052 --> 02:07:22,302
Keep her in for a week or two,
then set her free.

2361
02:07:24,802 --> 02:07:26,719
Okay, fine, let's meet halfway.

2362
02:07:27,552 --> 02:07:28,635
How about one month? Done?

2363
02:07:30,344 --> 02:07:31,344
Two months, final.

2364
02:07:31,844 --> 02:07:32,635
Attack!

2365
02:07:32,802 --> 02:07:34,219
[Grunts]

2366
02:08:01,260 --> 02:08:04,010
[growling]

2367
02:08:15,302 --> 02:08:17,010
[Screaming]

2368
02:08:30,802 --> 02:08:32,260
[Grunts]

2369
02:08:35,552 --> 02:08:39,677
You lost to a rookie Betaal who knows
no better than a newly-wed groom?

2370
02:08:41,427 --> 02:08:42,385
Pathetic!

2371
02:08:43,594 --> 02:08:44,510
Shame on you!

2372
02:08:44,802 --> 02:08:46,010
You've embarrassed me!

2373
02:08:47,510 --> 02:08:48,719
[Winces in pain]

2374
02:08:50,177 --> 02:08:51,052
Come to me...

2375
02:08:52,635 --> 02:08:53,510
Come.

2376
02:08:58,094 --> 02:08:59,594
[slurping]

2377
02:09:19,802 --> 02:09:20,927
[metal clanking]

2378
02:09:22,177 --> 02:09:23,177
Alok...

2379
02:09:23,260 --> 02:09:24,344
You can't...

2380
02:09:25,344 --> 02:09:26,385
You can't break them.

2381
02:09:29,385 --> 02:09:31,719
Alok... nobody can break them.

2382
02:09:32,260 --> 02:09:33,052
You should leave.

2383
02:09:33,135 --> 02:09:34,135
I won't!

2384
02:09:34,885 --> 02:09:35,969
I'm not going anywhere.

2385
02:09:37,135 --> 02:09:39,510
If I was meant to go,
I would have at the accident.

2386
02:09:41,094 --> 02:09:43,052
But your love saved me.

2387
02:09:43,969 --> 02:09:47,177
And now, nothing
in the world can keep us apart.

2388
02:09:47,260 --> 02:09:48,760
We can't fight this, Alok.

2389
02:09:48,791 --> 02:09:49,875
You should go.

2390
02:09:50,385 --> 02:09:51,719
Yakshasan is very powerful.

2391
02:09:51,744 --> 02:09:53,411
He can kill you too.

2392
02:09:54,927 --> 02:09:56,844
Take my advice... just go.
You should--

2393
02:09:56,927 --> 02:10:01,594
What worries do we have anymore?

2394
02:10:01,677 --> 02:10:06,135
We're ready to go through it all together

2395
02:10:06,302 --> 02:10:10,844
Forget about a 100 years

2396
02:10:10,969 --> 02:10:15,677
Can't fathom going a moment without you

2397
02:10:15,927 --> 02:10:20,760
Even this means
that we perish in this flame

2398
02:10:20,927 --> 02:10:25,719
Whether or not I am there with you.

2399
02:10:25,885 --> 02:10:30,719
Whether or not I am there with you.

2400
02:10:37,385 --> 02:10:38,927
So, you think,

2401
02:10:39,677 --> 02:10:40,969
you'll be able to live without me...

2402
02:10:42,302 --> 02:10:43,385
for hundred years?

2403
02:10:44,427 --> 02:10:45,594
Hundred years?!

2404
02:10:46,385 --> 02:10:47,844
It's hard to survive even
a second without you!

2405
02:10:50,760 --> 02:10:52,885
Yakshasan, you bloody...

2406
02:10:58,010 --> 02:10:59,094
What happened?

2407
02:11:00,094 --> 02:11:01,177
Why did you guys stop?

2408
02:11:01,594 --> 02:11:02,594
Continue.

2409
02:11:02,927 --> 02:11:06,510
Come on, I haven't seen any romance
in the past 75 years!

2410
02:11:07,802 --> 02:11:09,344
Keep going... continue.

2411
02:11:09,969 --> 02:11:10,927
Come down here...

2412
02:11:11,302 --> 02:11:12,469
I'll show you some real action too.

2413
02:11:12,802 --> 02:11:15,094
Action in romance... I love it!

2414
02:11:15,552 --> 02:11:16,885
[intense music]

2415
02:11:17,760 --> 02:11:19,052
[Grunts]

2416
02:11:23,177 --> 02:11:24,635
[growling]

2417
02:11:36,385 --> 02:11:37,844
[growling]

2418
02:11:38,219 --> 02:11:41,219
[Mystical song]

2419
02:11:42,427 --> 02:11:43,177
Hey...

2420
02:11:43,927 --> 02:11:45,510
You're not fit to be a Betaal.

2421
02:11:50,802 --> 02:11:52,344
[growling]

2422
02:12:02,635 --> 02:12:04,344
That lover of yours...

2423
02:12:05,385 --> 02:12:07,219
[Winces in pain]

2424
02:12:30,010 --> 02:12:32,135
Hundred years of toil and pain,

2425
02:12:34,010 --> 02:12:36,719
Hundred years bound in fire's chain,

2426
02:12:37,594 --> 02:12:39,385
Liberate the body's frame,

2427
02:12:40,094 --> 02:12:42,010
Liberate the soul the same.

2428
02:12:42,844 --> 02:12:44,469
Liberate the body's frame,

2429
02:12:45,135 --> 02:12:46,719
Liberate the soul the same.

2430
02:12:46,802 --> 02:12:47,969
[shackles unlocking]

2431
02:12:48,177 --> 02:12:49,760
[Gasping]

2432
02:12:55,260 --> 02:12:56,469
Remember...

2433
02:12:56,927 --> 02:12:58,927
I am your Thamma!

2434
02:12:59,927 --> 02:13:02,344
Your romeo seems to have gone pale.

2435
02:13:05,427 --> 02:13:06,510
[Grunts]

2436
02:13:09,177 --> 02:13:11,010
[growling]

2437
02:13:14,177 --> 02:13:15,844
[dramatic music]

2438
02:13:40,885 --> 02:13:43,094
[growling]

2439
02:13:46,177 --> 02:13:48,552
Thamma! Thamma!

2440
02:13:48,635 --> 02:13:50,885
[Winces in pain]

2441
02:14:00,302 --> 02:14:02,094
[Gasping]

2442
02:14:18,635 --> 02:14:20,510
Let this be a warning
to every single one of you.

2443
02:14:21,802 --> 02:14:27,260
Defy your Thamma and your fate
will be the same as his.

2444
02:14:29,344 --> 02:14:31,427
You actually believed you
could stand against Yakshasan, huh?

2445
02:14:31,719 --> 02:14:32,885
[evil laughter]

2446
02:14:36,927 --> 02:14:38,385
[sad music]

2447
02:14:43,969 --> 02:14:44,844
Alok...

2448
02:14:44,927 --> 02:14:46,594
Alok! Alok!

2449
02:14:46,677 --> 02:14:48,260
Alok! Alok!

2450
02:14:48,344 --> 02:14:49,344
No... no... no... no way!
Alok!

2451
02:14:49,635 --> 02:14:51,344
Alok! Alok!

2452
02:14:51,969 --> 02:14:52,969
Alok!

2453
02:14:52,994 --> 02:14:54,036
ALOK!!!

2454
02:14:55,552 --> 02:14:57,885
[Screaming]

2455
02:15:14,344 --> 02:15:16,927
[Mystical song]

2456
02:15:26,302 --> 02:15:27,802
[Winces in pain]

2457
02:15:47,844 --> 02:15:49,719
[growling]

2458
